title: date nut bread
directions: Pour the boiling water over dates and let stand. Beat egg until light. Add the sugar gradually. Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Add dates and flour alternately into egg mixture. Stir in the melted butter and vanilla. Pour in 8 x 8 pan or 2 bread tins, greased. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus and pasta
directions: Cook asparagus in small amount of water, 8 minutes until tender or in a microwave.
In saucepan, cook ham, onion and celery in margarine for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add cream, nutmeg, pepper and Fontina cheese.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cooked asparagus.
Toss asparagus mixture, Parmesan cheese and drained pasta until coated.
Serve immediately.

title: icebox dessert
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks, one at a time.
Add pineapple and pecans (drain pineapple well).
Whip egg whites real stiff.
Fold in mixture slowly.
Stack with whole graham crackers (for bottom, middle and top layer).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: freezer cucumber pickles
directions: Layer cucumbers, onions and salt in a baking dish. Refrigerate 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
At the same time, in a small saucepan bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over drained vegetables. Stir well and pack into freezer jars leaving 1/4-inch head space. Store in freezer.
Thaw in refrigerator and serve chilled.
Yields 3 pints.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 10 minutes.
Strain out spice. Serve in bowl decorated with holly or other Christmas greens.

title: juna's no fail popcorn balls
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, add sugar, molasses and water; boil slowly for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Turn off heat.
Add baking soda. It will foam.
Pour over corn; stir until corn is covered.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil vinegar, etc., together and pour over warmed beets.
Put in prepared jars and seal airtight.

title: "fresh" cherry pie
directions: Mix together and let set while preparing crust.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate and dot with 3 tablespoons butter.
Adjust top; seal with fluted edges.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel, core and half apples and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir together both sugars, salt and flour and sprinkle half of mixture over apples.
Dot each apple with butter.
Mix vanilla with water; drizzle half of liquid over apples.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture over apples and other half of liquid mix.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: poultry seasoning
directions: Combine and shake well.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: "mock" lobster(from binghamton, new york 1963 newspaper)
directions: Put cod into a pan; cover with cold water.
Add salt.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cover the cod with cold water.
Add vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 more minutes.
Drain.

title: lisa west's microwave hamburger stroganoff
directions: Microwave hamburger on High for 5 minutes; stir.
Add onion and margarine and microwave on High 2 minutes and stir.
Blend in flour, garlic, pepper and soup.
Heat on High for 3 to 4 minutes until thickened, stirring 1 or 2 times.
Blend in sour cream (if using nonfat, add water to desired consistency).
Microwave on Medium-high 1 minute.
Serve over noodles (can substitute Butter Buds for margarine).

title: chicken louisiana
directions: Using a heavy skillet, saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in 2 teaspoons olive oil until the onion is soft - about 5 minutes.

Remove vegetables from the skillet and place in a dish. Add 2 teaspoons olive oil to the skillet, sprinkle the chicken breasts with the paprika and cayenne pepper and cook in skillet on medium high heat, turning as needed; cook for about 5 minutes. Add back about half of the cooked vegetables to the chicken.
Add the tomatoes, rosemary, marjoram, and bay leaves; reduce the heat, cover and simmer for about 10 minutes or until the chicken is fork-tender.
Whisk together the flour and chicken broth (or water), add to the skillet and stir the mixture constantly until it has thickened - about 3 minutes.
Add the remaining cooked vegetables to the mixture and heat for a couple of minutes. Remove the bay leaves and serve with or over rice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pie shell according to directions for empty baked crust.
Chop 1 cup of strawberries.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water gradually until smooth.
Add chopped strawberries.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat. Stir in food coloring.
Cool in refrigerator 1/2 hour.
tags: Pet-Ritz deep dish pie crust shell

title: favorite beef loaf
directions: Soak cracker crumbs in milk; add meat, eggs, onions and seasonings.
Mix well.
Shape into loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 50.

title: broiled fish
directions: Place top oven rack 4 to 5-inches from heat source.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all together and marinate 3 to 4 days.
Turn or shake each day. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peach crisp
directions: Toss peaches with 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon into a lightly-greased, 8 or 9-inch baking dish and set aside.

title: supper in a dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Layer with vegetables according to your taste.
Pour soup over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle cheese on top and return to oven until melted.

title: cheese cake ala ryan
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time. Separate 1/3 batter and add chocolate to it.
Spoon batters into buttered pans placed in water.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Makes 1 1/2 cakes (put in pie pans).

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and sugar.
Simmer, stirring often, for 45 minutes.
Stir in oregano and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Beat eggs.
Dip eggplant into eggs, then into flour.
Brown the slices in remaining oil.

title: minted berry soup
directions: Wash and hull berries.
Crush berries lightly with a fork. Place in a saucepan; stir in brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add Sauterne; bring to a boil.
Add chopped mint; simmer 2 or 3 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add oil and buttermilk.
Pour liquid ingredients over flour mixture; store in refrigerator until ready to use. Roll out as needed and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening in a large bowl.
Add sugars gradually, beating until well blended.
Beat in egg, vanilla and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (15 minutes).
Yields 5 dozen.

title: apple treats
directions: Cut and core apples into quarters.
Separate crescent rolls. Roll each apple quarter separately in a roll.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in a small bowl.
Then roll apples and rolls in the mixture. Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 10 to 20 minutes until apples are done and rolls are brown.

title: ice cream yum-yums
directions: You will need an ice cream scoop, small saucepan, wooden spoon, measuring cups and knife.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix well & serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Add ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Place chicken in casserole or baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour.
Add more sauce, if necessary.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix well together and chill.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In skillet, cook onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in hot Crisco until tender but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and Tabasco sauce. Simmer uncovered for 45 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with water; stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add shrimp; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon over hot rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: For the gravy, brown the 1/4 cup of butter with the flour in a 3-quart saucepan, then add condensed beef stock and cook on low heat, about 5 minutes.
Heat 1/4 cup butter in a large skillet and quickly brown sirloin strips.
Add sliced mushrooms, chopped onion, garlic powder and parsley and cook about 15 minutes or until brown, then add the gravy mixture, sherry and tomato puree.
Cook until meat is tendered, uncovered, stirring occasionally, then stir in the dairy sour cream and bring almost to a boil.
Serve stroganoff over buttered noodles.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with flour and nuts; cook 20 minutes at 300°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread over crust.
Then add strawberries and glaze. Chill.

title: sugar-free tropical spaghetti squash
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: mother's fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix fruit and nuts.
Put part of flour on fruit and nuts before putting into batter so they don't stick together.
Mix rest of ingredients with fruit and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake on a greased pan at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix brown sugar, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and mustard
together
until
sugar is dissolved.
Pour over beans and mix
onion into mixture.
Break up 3 strips of fried bacon and combine
with mixture.
Place 2 fried bacon strips on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: granny luster's mckinley pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until mixture thickens and crust is a golden brown.

title: oatmeal raisin pudding cookie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and pudding in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs; add flour, then stir in oats and raisins. Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat meat with flour with salt in it.
Brown meat and chopped onion in oil in a large skillet.
Add bouillon, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add vegetables; simmer 30 more minutes or until tender.

title: plum nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix in liquid ingredients, adding plums and nuts last.
Add 1 cup raisins, if desired.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot dogs
directions: Cook hot dogs on the grill full blast until black.
Put in buns.
Cover all black areas with ketchup, then cover ketchup with a layer of mustard.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread into small pieces and moisten with milk. Add remaining ingredients and combine thoroughly. Shape into patties about 2-inches in diameter and either fry in hot oil or broil on lightly oiled broiler pan at 400° for 12 minutes. Turn cakes halfway through cooking time.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up broccoli, cauliflower and lettuce in small pieces.
Add green onions, carrots and cheese.
Cut dried beef up in small pieces, also.
Mix with dressing.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Add minced onion to water.
When done, cool.
Break into shredded consistency.
Add Ortega Mexican chicken, water and black olives; mix together.
Simmer on low for about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve warm.
Can serve with tortillas.

title: munnie's english gingerbread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients and mix with raisins and pecans.
Make syrup of 2 cups ribbon cane syrup, 2 sticks oleo and 1 cup sugar. Bring to a rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Pour slowly over 4 beaten eggs while continuing to beat.
Add flour mixture to syrup and stir.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 small tube pans.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Put a pan of hot water in bottom of oven to bake cake.
Before serving sprinkle with

title: polish doughnuts
directions: Scald milk and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in milk.
Add 2 cups
flour and beat well.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Add melted margarine, egg and egg yolks (well beaten), sugar, salt, vanilla and grated orange rind.
Beat well.

title: summer squash dressing(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery until tender.
Add cornbread and mix well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: cherry winks
directions: Place margarine and sugar into a small bowl and beat.
Add egg, nuts and cherries.
Reduce speed to slow and fold in flour.
Roll into small balls.
Rolls balls in corn flakes.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Decorate with a cherry or walnut.
Bake at 350 for 15-20 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: In heavy skillet, brown ground beef, onion, celery, mushrooms, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato puree.
Add seasonings and cover; simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Add kidney beans and adjust seasoning.
Continue to simmer 30 minutes longer.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
Good served over rice.

title: orange sour cream cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, orange rind and sour cream.
Stir in dry ingredients, blending well.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Top with frosting while still warm.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce for fifty
directions: Brown beef.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining sauce ingredients to cooked beef.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently, until thickened, approximately 1/2 hour.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Bring 5 gallons water to boil.
Add 5 ounces salt and 3 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Add pasta gradually while stirring. Return to a fast boil.
Cook uncovered until tender but firm, approximately 10 minutes.
Serve 6 ounces sauce over 4 ounces spaghetti.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 3 layers.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Saute onions, celery, garlic and chopped bell pepper in a heavy pot in the margarine or canola oil until wilted.
Add Worcestershire sauce, crabmeat and season to taste with salt, red pepper and black pepper.
Cook over medium heat about 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Then add buns which have been soaked in the milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Stuff crab shells with mixture.
Use artificial crab shells.
Sprinkle tops of stuffed crabs with bread crumbs and bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes or until well browned.
Stuffs 12 crab shells.

title: tomato and bacon pasta salad
directions: Saute bacon 5 minutes until browned; remove bacon with slotted spoon to cup lined with paper towel.
Discarding all but 1 tablespoon fat, heat skillet on medium-high and saute tomatoes one minute.
Add garlic; saute 30 seconds.
Add pepper, oil and vinegar and mix well.
Place remaining ingredients in serving bowl; top
with bacon and tomato and mix and toss.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes. When cool, add chopped eggs, pickles, onion, mustard, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Mix well.

title: bev's chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown chicken.
Add diced pepper, cream cheese and Pace picante to skillet.
Heat until smooth.
Fill flour tortillas with mix. Roll up and place in baking pan.
Cover with enchilada sauce and shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake(makes 12 servings)
directions: To Make Cake:
In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar and salt.
In saucepan, over medium-high heat, heat water, 1/2 cup (1 stick) spread, oil and 1/4 cup cocoa to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour into flour mixture, stirring until smooth.
Blend in buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, 1 teaspoon vanilla and vinegar until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in water until done, about 10 minutes.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Gradually add each of the remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.

title: the good cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press each ball with the bottom of a small glass. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
After they have cooled (5 to 10 minutes), dip in powdered sugar.
Very good.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli only until soft.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix all together into a casserole dish.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan, if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be prepared earlier and put into freezer.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in oven dish.
Add soup, adding no water.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potato slices until crisp-tender.
Place slices in greased casserole (2-quart).
Mix all remaining ingredients; pour over potatoes.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 1 1/2 hours or 45 minutes at 1 hour.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, cheese mixture from cheese cake mix and milk until smooth.
Line ladyfingers on bottom and around sides of a spring-form pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture in pan. Put in refrigerator for about 8 hours.
Before serving, pour topping of your choice on top.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef and chopped onion in a small amount of fat in a heavy skillet until the meat has turned white.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Put into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: venison burgers
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make patties and fry in pan or bake in oven at 350°.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter until light and fluffy.
Add powdered sugar and salt and mix well.
Blend in flour.
Stir in water, vanilla and peanuts.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten slightly.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Dredge cookie in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Follow directions on box of roll mix. Set aside in a covered bowl.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place melted margarine.
Add syrup and brown sugar.
Sprinkle nuts, if desired.
After dough rises, roll out on floured surface approximately 9 x 24-inch shape. Sprinkle granulated sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Roll up like jelly roll and cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in syrup, 4 down and 6 across. Cover and let rise. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: cream soup substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients using blender or food processor. Store in an airtight container.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all together and fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: dirt dessert cups
directions: Pour cold milk into large bowl, add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and half of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon cookies into cups.
Fill cups 3/4 full of pudding mixture.
Top with remaining cookies. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: cabbage deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter; add flour, salt, pepper and mustard, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Add milk, stirring until thickened.
Add egg yolk, stirring constantly, and cook for 1 minute.
Place in a baking dish by layers:
half of the cabbage, onions, cheese and cream sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top the mixture with bread crumbs.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Then uncover and bake for an additional 5 minutes.

title: fruit medley
directions: In a large bowl combine pie filling and canned fruit. Cover and refrigerate. Stir in bananas just before serving.

title: mediterranean melange for new year's eve
directions: Cook the macaroni and drain.
Brown the ground beef and drain. Combine the macaroni, the cooked ground beef, mushroom pieces, sliced black olives and enough spaghetti sauce to make a Sloppy Joes consistency.
Heat to simmering.
Add the cubed cheese and continue heating only until the cheese starts to melt.
Remove from heat and serve with garlic bread.

title: potato bake
directions: Boil potatoes, just until done.
Drain.
Put in a baking dish.
Add
liquid ranch dressing and bacon bits to the potatoes. Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese is bubbly. Delicious!

title: old fashioned brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: party punch
directions: Mix water, sugar and Kool-Aid until sugar and Kool-Aid is dissolved.
Add juice.
Stir well and freeze.
Add ginger ale before serving.
Remove frozen mixture 2 hours before serving. Thaw until soft.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, peanut butter, syrup and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add oats, soda and salt. Stir with a spoon.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Measure 1/2 cup for each cookie.
Place dough 4-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press dough into a circle with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Centers will be soft.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; chop into bite size pieces. Mix all other ingredients except corn flakes. Take 1 cup corn flakes and stir into casserole. Take other cup and mix with melted butter. Place on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients in mixer.
Pour into loaf pan.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar, vanilla, eggs and butter.
Melt chocolate squares and mix together.
Add flour, 1/2 cup chocolate chips, pecans and marshmallows.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remainder of chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: e-z sweet potato biscuits
directions: Skin the sweet potato and mash it in a medium bowl.
Add egg, butter, milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
If you have a KitchenAid mixer, place this mixture in it and attach the dough hook.
Start adding the Bisquick and add enough until you form a dough like mixture consistency.
Let this work the dough for about 1 minute.
This makes a nice soft dough.
Roll out dough to about 1/2 inch thickness and using your biscuit cutter, cut out your biscuits.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 400 degrees for about 12 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are lightly browned.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put
hash
browns
in
a large casserole dish.	Mix and heat in large pan, soup, water, margarine, onions, sour cream and cheese,
salt
and	pepper to taste.
Pour heated mix over potatoes and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients (you may add any ingredients you prefer). Top with mayonnaise. Sprinkle sugar on top. Add cheese and finish with bacon bits. Cover and chill before serving.

title: makay's husband's beef and zucchini delight
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.
Add mushrooms and simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, add stew beef and let stand until one hour before serving time.
In a separate container cook zucchini until done but firm.
Shortly before serving, add both kinds of cheese to sauce and meat, mix thoroughly and heat to desired serving temperature.
Arrange your favorite shape pasta which you have found the time to cook at some point along the way on a serving platter.
Add zucchini slices and top with the sauce/beef mixture.
Crushed fresh parsley and finely chopped ripe olives may be sprinkled over the top.
Yield is 4 generous servings.

title: malasadas(fried dough)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and flour.
Add melted butter and 1 cup warm milk (if desired).
Mix yeast in warm water; add salt.
Combine all ingredients.
Let rise.
Warm 48 ounces of oil on medium-high heat. When oil is hot, break dough and fry until brown on both sides. Remove and sprinkle with sugar.
Enjoy.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread well drained
and
squeezed dry kraut on 1 slice bread. Lay cheese
on
top.
Spread corned beef on other half of bread. Butter
both
sides
of bread and brown in skillet. This can be prepared
and
put in freezer until ready to heat again in oven and served hot.
Keep warm in bun warmer.

title: reese's peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cut cookie dough into 9 equal slices.
Cut each slice into 4 equal parts.
Put each quarter into a greased miniature muffin pan.
Bake for 8 minutes or until straw color.
Immediately press 1 Reese's miniature peanut cup into middle of each cookie.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: cheese filled triangles
directions: In processor bowl, combine cheeses, eggs and pepper.
Process until smooth.
Prepare 40 small fillo triangles according to directions on package. Fill each triangle with 1/2 teaspoon of cheese mixture. Brush outside of triangles with butter.
Place, seam side down, on cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown and puffed.
Serve hot.

title: taco soup
directions: Simmer for about 1 to 2 hours.
Good with lite corn chips or French bread.
You can sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: spice orange coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
To serve, spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons mix and 3/4 cup boiling water together.
Mix and enjoy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread, eggs and milk.
In a casserole dish, crumble 3 slices of bread in bottom of dish. Spoon mixed ingredients over crumbled bread.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour over mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (Crumble rest of bread on top of casserole before baking.)

title: chicken pie
directions: Place alternate layers of chicken, celery, crumbs and parsley in a greased bread pan.
Add salt and eggs to chicken stock; mix well and pour over chicken.
Bake in a pan of hot water at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Cover with pastry crust cut in 2-inch rounds.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix together eggs, Parmesan cheese and oil.
Stir in Bisquick and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese tea balls
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar, flour and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and roll into ball.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix in blender or with wire whisk.

title: rotel chicken #1
directions: Season chicken in 2-quarts water.
Cook until tender.
Debone chicken. Cook vermicelli in broth. Saute peppers and onions in oleo.
Mix all ingredients. Top casserole with can of Durkee onion rings. Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in casserole.
Spread barbecue sauce over chops.
Pour 2 cups water over top.
Bake at 300° to 350° until tender.

title: exciting dream pie
directions: Beat Dream
Whip with 1 cup milk and vanilla in a large mixer bowl
at
high
speed (about 6 minutes) or until topping thickens and
forms peaks.
Add remaining milk and pie filling mix.	Mix at	low
speed
then
at
high speed for 2 minutes, scraping
bowl occasionally.
Spoon
into
cooked
pie shell. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients until blended.
Add the nuts and raisins.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add all ingredients, except chips and cheese, and bring mixture to a full boil.
Place 1/2 of mixture in baking dish, cover with Doritos, add other 1/2 of mixture and top with grated cheese.
Place in oven long enough for cheese to melt. Eat with extra chips.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water until tender (8 to 10 minutes).
Combine onions, pepper and carrots in large bowl; toss.
Combine rest of the ingredients until smooth (blender works well).
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight or longer.
Drain before serving (save marinade and return leftovers to marinade).

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except pineapple chunks.
Top salad with pineapple chunks.
May use any flavor jello.

title: hot gingered fruit
directions: Drain all fruits, reserving 2 tablespoons of pineapple juice. Pat all fruit dry with paper towel.
Arrange fruit in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cherries.
Combine sugar and butter with 2 tablespoons of pineapple juice.
Add ginger.
Cook over low heat until sugar melts; pour over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: green tomato catsup
directions: Put layers of vegetables in a pan.
Sprinkle salt over; let stand overnight.
Drain all water off.
Mix the sugar and vinegar. Cook them slowly for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit punch
directions: Put sugar and water in pot; boil and let cool. In a blender, blend bananas in pineapple juice; leave some banana chunks. Do Not puree. Add banana mixture, orange juice and lemon juice to sugar water. Mix and freeze in shallow pan. Add 7-up 25 minutes before serving.

title: republican cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar and add alternately with milk to sugar mixture.
Beat whites and fold into mixture.
Flavor to taste.
Bake in layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until done in middle.
Cool.
Spread with jelly and dust with 10x sugar.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand.
Beat eggs lightly. Beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, soda, salt, and cinnamon.

title: oven-fried sesame chicken
directions: Place soy sauce in shallow dish; add chicken, turning to coat. Remove chicken; discard soy sauce.
Combine sesame seed, flour and pepper in huge Ziploc plastic bag.
Add chicken all at once to bag. Shake to coat.
Spray baking dish with vegetable cooking spray. Place chicken in baking dish.
Drizzle margarine over chicken. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: german chocolate cream pie
directions: Prepare baked pie shell and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
In a medium bowl, beat milk and egg yolks until smooth.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture thickens and comes to a full boil.
Stir and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Make hole in center.
Add Crisco, boiling water and baking soda.
Beat egg and add to mixture, along with baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well and bake in 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate-dipped strawberries
directions: Melt the chocolate slowly in a double boiler, taking care to keep it from getting too hot.
Choose berries with the stems intact.
Rinse berries and drain to remove any trace of moisture.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins; drain, slice thin and set aside. Pan-fry bacon; add onion.
Saute until brown.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper; stir in vinegar and water.
Add to bacon mixture gradually and cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Add celery seed and potatoes and heat thoroughly over low heat. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: spicy barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, on broiler rack.
Rub well with cut lemon.
Brush with 3/4 cup sauce.
Broil 7 to 9-inches from heat for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken, rub again with lemon and sauce.
Broil for 15 to 30 minutes longer or until tender, well browned and crisp. Garnish with parsley.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Add butter and blend with fingers.
Form a crust in a greased cake pan (9 x 13-inches).
Push up sides of pan (approximately 3/4-inch).
Bake crust at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs.
Add to meat and remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup catsup which is spread on top of loaf.
Put in a 9 x 3 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and form small meatballs (about the size of a walnut).
Place meatballs on greased cookie sheet and bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Drain grease.
In a saucepan, blend flour with tomato juice.
Add barbecue sauce and water. Stir over low heat until slightly thickened.
Pour over drained meatballs and continue baking for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix all ingredients. Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes. Cut into rectangles about 2 x 1-inch. Refrigerate any remaining appetizers.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: pumpkin pie(yields 2 pies)
directions: Cook and drain the pumpkin, then run through colander.
Mix ingredients well. Place in two pie shells.
Cook at 350° until firm.
Don't overcook.

title: german nut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream; beat well.
Add flour and baking powder.
Beat thoroughly.
Fold in nuts and cherries.

title: jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg yolks until thick; add soda, both sugars and butter.
Beat until creamy; add spices and vanilla.
Add jam, nuts and beaten egg whites.
Fold in flour and milk.
Pour into tube or loaf pan.
Bake.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Melt oleo, add cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes in 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet with sides.

title: potato and eggs
directions: Potatoes peeled and cut in small pieces.
Fry them just like you do when you make fried potatoes.
Once they are fried, place them on a dish and take most of the oil out of the frypan.
Now take eggs and mix them good and you can add a bit of salt.
Put the potatoes back in the frypan and pour the mixed eggs over the potatoes.
Once it browns on one side, turn and cook other side. When you are frying the potatoes when they are almost done, you can put some diced up onion in too, that is if you like onion.
You can also add some grated cheese to the eggs.

title: hot baked fruit
directions: Put prunes, apricots and pineapple in a deep 9-inch round casserole.
Combine cherries and water and pour over fruit, mixing well.
Stir in almonds.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grandma whittlesey's no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa together.
Cook in medium-size pan at medium heat to boiling.
Stir for 1 1/2 minutes while boiling.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper. Refrigerate to harden.
Or you may spread mixture in cake pan for cookie squares.

title: pumpkin bar
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients, except nuts.
Blend dry and wet ingredients well.
Add nuts, saving 1/4 cup to sprinkle on top of frosting, if desired.
Bake in an ungreased 11 x 17 x 1-inch baking pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal and chopped onion.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Spoon out and drop into hot cooking oil.
Cook until brown.

title: microwave vegetable platter
directions: Select a 10-inch glass platter. Arrange broccoli pieces around outside edge; then cauliflower, carrots and pepper in circles, with squash in the center.
Dot with butter slices.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 5 to 7 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper before serving.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all together and fry like small pancakes.

title: spiced beef
directions: Slice roast beef, then cut into julienne strips.
Place in a flat dish (Pyrex baking dish).
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Add other ingredients and pour Wish-Bone dressing over all.
Chill overnight, mixing or turning a few times.
To serve, place beef over a bed of shredded lettuce and garnish with a border of chopped fresh tomatoes and black olives.
Serve with hot crusty bread.

title: rhubarb-apple crisp
directions: Mix together the rhubarb, apples, sugar and 1/2 cup flour; set aside.
Blend together 1 1/2 cups flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, cinnamon, salt and margarine.
Press half of that mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour rhubarb and apple mixture over that; cover with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until brown.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased pan until knife comes out clean.

title: pear cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add a third at a time to other mixture. Mix nuts with last third of flour.
Add to mixture.
Add grated and drained pears to mixture.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Bake in tube pan for about 55 minutes.

title: creamy buttercream icing
directions: Cream thoroughly crisco and dream whip.
Add the remaining ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Can be refrigerated 2 to 3 months in Tupperware.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Blend corn syrup and peanut butter. Gradually blend in eggs and sugar until smooth, stir in vanilla and salt.
Arrange peanuts on bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour peanut butter mixture over peanuts.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 25 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream shortening with sugar, beat until well mixed.
Beat in egg, add yeast mixture and beat until well mixed.
Add salt and flour, working in until a smooth dough is formed.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Roll and form rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chinese beets heloise
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1 1/2 cups of beet liquid.
Place beets in a medium saucepan with the reserved liquid and the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Then cook for 3 minutes over medium heat or until mixture thickens.
Let cool, then store in refrigerator. It keeps 6 weeks or longer.

title: molded cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot water. Add vinegar, onion and seasoning. Chill until thick, then add finely chopped cucumber and chill until firm.

title: french fried zucchini sticks
directions: If
the
kids
won't
eat
vegetables,
try
this.
Cut zucchini lengthwise
into
sticks
about
the
size
of thick, country-style French
fries.
Lay
the sticks on paper towels. Sprinkle fairly
heavily with salt and let stand about 1 hour. Pat sticks dry and shake them in a bag with flour and a little fresh-ground pepper.
Fry the zucchini in batches, don't crowd them, in
hot deep oil (365°) until golden.
(To conserve oil, you can
use
a
medium-size,
heavy skillet instead of a deep fryer. Fill
skillet
with
about 1 1/2 inches of oil.) Drain the sticks on
paper towels laid over newspaper and salt very lightly.
Keep the
sticks
hot in a slow oven.
Serve them as hot as
possible. For
grownups,
the
sticks
are
good with cocktails, either plain or with Turkish Yogurt Sauce.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and shortening in large saucepan.
Over low heat, stir in cocoa.
Remove from heat and add sugar, eggs and vanilla, mixing thoroughly.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into chocolate mixture.
Add nuts and mix well.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread on frosting while brownies are warm.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: old fashion potato soup
directions: Put all vegetables together and add salt, pepper, celery salt and small piece of bacon or butter.
Cover with a quart of water. Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Blend flour with milk.
Add to hot soup. Stir until comes to a boil.
Cook for a few minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Sprinkle Accent and pepper over chicken.
Cook in oil over medium heat until white and opaque, turning once (about 6 minutes total).
Remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
Cook asparagus by package directions, 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: surprise quiche
directions: Thaw spinach about 2 to 3 hours.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and mix.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.	For 1 cup of hot chocolate, use
heaping
tablespoonfuls
of mix to a cup of hot water. Makes a gallon of dry mix.

title: picadillo puerto viallrta(mexican hash)
directions: Heat the oil, in a large, heavy skillet, and brown the meat, then add the onions and garlic.
When brown, add all the other ingredients, except the almonds, and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Simmer gently, uncovered, until cooked or about 20 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Follow directions on yeast package for dissolving yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients together and roll out like biscuits. Cut with large biscuit cutter.
Fold over when putting in pan.
Let rise only once.
After they have risen, bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400° to 425° until brown.
Makes 12 large rolls.

title: filled hot dogs
directions: Mix all together.
Take hot dog bun and hollow out.
Fill bun with mixture, wrap in foil and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Cook zucchini in lemon juice until tender.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Simmer for one minute.
Add crumb mixture (to thicken).

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut fruit and nuts.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Mix 1/2 of flour mixture with fruit and nuts.
Cream butter, adding sugar.
Beat eggs into mixture.
Add half of flour and rest of ingredients; mix well.
Drop in ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable hamburger soup
directions: Cook hamburger in water for 15 minutes, breaking it into pieces.
Add all other ingredients and cook until tender.

title: chicken wings
directions: Place chicken in greased baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together well and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: lemonade
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice and cool. Dilute with ice water when ready to serve.

title: green beans almondine
directions: Cook beans in own liquid about 30 minutes, drain.
Meanwhile, cook almonds in butter over low heat until golden, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Pour over hot beans.
Makes 7 to 8 servings.

title: no bake "icebox" fruitcake
directions: In extra large bowl or pan, crush graham crackers (very fine). Add pecans, raisins, dates and cherries.
Melt marshmallows and condensed milk in microwave at least 8 minutes (or more). Immediately fold into mixture very quickly.
Use sterilized hands only, no spoons!
Very hard to mix!!!
Will have a sticky texture. Press into (any shape) plastic container lined with wax paper. Pack firmly to stick together in shape of container.
Freeze; will keep several weeks.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt cheese and add a little milk until creamy.
Add to hamburger.	Keep hot in crock-pot.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix. Grease a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet and line with wax paper.
Pour mixture on cookie sheet and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn onto towel sprinkled with granulated sugar and cool.

title: greek pita bread sandwiches
directions: Combine wine, oil, minced garlic, oregano, salt and pepper. Marinate steak strips, covered, overnight in refrigerator.
Drain meat.
Cook in melted butter.
Fill pita bread pockets with meat, lettuce, tomatoes, cucumbers, onions, sour cream and parsley.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crushed corn flakes. Make into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls into crushed corn flakes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Top with pecan halves, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or less.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter, over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Can be served over noodles or rice.

title: tangy oven beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large oven casserole; cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Can bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: maw-maw wright's biscuits
directions: You will also need a good "seasoned" iron skillet.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water.
Cook until soft. Dissolve flour in milk, then add that and all other ingredients to potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 10 more minutes.

title: whatever(tastes like peanut brittle!)
directions: Line a large jelly roll pan with foil.
Break graham crackers into small sections and line pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter, milk, sugar and cocoa.
Cook in double boiler until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop on wax paper.
Allow time to harden.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put oil and dry onion soup mix in a bag; shake.
Pour in a baking dish.
Cover and cook about 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix broth and soup.
Put in bottom of pan.
Add chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with flour and buttermilk.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: angel-pecan pie
directions: Mix together in order listed.
Pour into greased pie pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Whip 1 cup whipping cream.
Pour over pie.
Let stand.
Refrigerate 2 to 8 hours before serving.

title: super bowl chili
directions: Dice and saute first 5 ingredients.
Add meat and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add water just to cover top.
Cook 3 hours on low heat.
Stir often.
Add hot peppers and Tabasco until eyes water.

title: soy marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes enough for 3 pound steak.
Put in plastic bag or non-metal container.
Turn meat occasionally.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator or 2 to 3 hours at room temperature. Remove from plastic bag. Pat dry. Fix as you like.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cream well.
Sift together flour and salt.
Stir in first mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Chill dough. Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes in 400° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar as soon as the cookies are done.
Let cool and roll in sugar once more.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Parboil cabbage and onions for 7 minutes; drain.
Make a white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and pepper.
Add 1/2 pound of cubed cheese.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Layer half of cabbage mixture, bread and 1/3 of sausage into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Repeat layer of cabbage, layer of sausage and layer of bread.
Top with sauce and remaining sausage.

title: grandmother's salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and add oil gradually.
Use on electric mixer or blender to beat until well blended.
Keeps well if refrigerated in a tightly covered jar.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: crunchy hush puppies
directions: Sift corn meal and flour together. Stir in onions. Mix milk, egg and 1 tbsp. oil together. Heat 2 cups oil in heavy duty sauce pan. Oil should be at least 3 inches deep so hush puppies will be round. Pour milk mixture into corn meal and flour and stir. Immediately drop by teaspoonful into hot oil; cook until brown (about 1 minute). Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. Serve hot.

title: stuffed tofu(tofu nhoe)
directions: Prepare rice and set aside.
In a small bowl, soak tree ears in hot water until softened, about 2 minutes.
Drain, rinse, cut off the hard knobs and chop coarse.
Set aside.
Mix pork, onion, pepper, 1 tablespoon fish sauce, dried tree ears and m.s.g. in medium bowl.
Use a teaspoon, spoon the center of each cut tofu, leaving a small hole.
(Be careful not to spoon all the way to the bottom of the tofu).
Cover the tofu hole with meat mixtures.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat, heat the oil until hot.
Add tofu and fry until golden brown, about 5 minutes per side.
Add tomatoes and remaining fish sauce into the tofu skillet and simmer, stirring a few times, for about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add green onions.
Serve hot with rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit cake (white) 7 pounds
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat eggs lightly and add to butter and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; then add alternately with orange juice to batter.
Put glazed fruits in large pan; dust flour all over the fruit.
Mix and stir; add to batter with raisins and nuts and mix well.
Grease pan and line with waxed paper.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
A pan of water should be placed on the oven floor for best results.
When done, remove from pan to cool.

title: apfelshnitten*(apple strips)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, mix flour, salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cut in Crisco.
Mix together egg yolk and milk and add to crumbled mixture. Form into ball.
Take out half and roll on floured board.
Put this on 15 x 10-inch pan.
Place cereal mixture into bottom, distribute apples and add sugar and spices.
Roll out rest of dough and cover, as in a pie.
Brush top with beaten egg white.
Bake 40 minutes.
Yields 25 (2 x 3-inch) pieces.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan; cook over low heat about 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken, ribs, etc, and bake.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and sweet potatoes, orange juice and rind, salt and spices.
Mix well; add evaporated milk and mix until blended.
Pour into 2 pastry lined pie pans and bake one hour or until firm.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 2 (9-inch) round pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: hobo veggies
directions: Slice and layer potatoes, carrots and onions in roast pan. Dot with margarine. Cover and bake at 425° until tender, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Combine the ingredients and refrigerate.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Mix pasta and all other ingredients together with 1/2 pint mayonnaise and refrigerate 8 hours.
Make 1 large bowl of salad.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Thoroughly chill can of milk in refrigerator overnight. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add honey, salt and juice. When it has congealed, lightly beat milk until stiff and whip gelatin mixture into it.
Spread half of crumbs in a cake pan (10 x 13 1/2-inch).
Pour mixture over the crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs and set in refrigerator to chill (approximately 3 hours). May be served plain or with whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; pick off bone.
Mix bite size pieces of chicken, rice, celery, salad dressing, lemon juice, soup and broth.
Place in casserole dish.
Melt oleo and pour over Rice Krispies.
Spread over the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together flour, salt and powdered alum.
Add vegetable oil.
Stir in boiling water.
Mix food coloring after boiling water.
Mix or knead until smooth.
Store in airtight container.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Combine brown sugar, cream of tartar, water and egg whites in top of double boiler.
Stir to mix; place over hot water and beat with rotary beater or mixer until frosting holds peaks (about 7 minutes).
Stir in vanilla.

title: nutty apple cake with cream cheese topping
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar until foamy. Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together tomato soup, water and flour until smooth. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Place in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over noodles, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: porcupine beef balls
directions: Combine rice, beef, salt, pepper and onion. Mix, shape into 12 balls. Brown balls in vegetable oil in frying pan, add tomato soup and water. Cover, cook 40 minutes over low heat until rice is tender. Serves six.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cottage cheese in food processor; blend well.
Add the sour cream, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Chill until ready to use.
Use fresh fruits to dip into the chilled dip.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add to 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with chicken.
Spread cheese over chicken.
Mix mayo, soup and milk together and pour over all.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crazy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over butter.
Pour fruit over flour mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Put lemonade and milk in blender until thick (less than 1 minute).
Add whipped topping and fold together.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill overnight.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well.
Then add hot, hot tap water, a tablespoon at a time, until you have a sticky consistency.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, salt, flour and butter.
Stirring well, add nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and at 300° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Drop frankfurters into saucepan of boiling water (2 cups). Lower heat, cover and simmer 5 to 8 minutes.
Spread each slice of bread with soft butter and mustard.
Place bread slices on baking sheet.
Top each slice with cheese.
Place a frankfurter on top of each cheese slice.
Fold over to make a triangle shape.
Fasten with wooden picks.

title: green bean, walnut and feta salad
directions: Drop beans into large pot of boiling water; cook until crisp-tender, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water to stop the cooking process.
Pat dry with paper towels. Combine oil, parsley, vinegar, salt, garlic and pepper; blend well.
Arrange beans in shallow serving dish.
Sprinkle with nuts, onion and Feta.
Just before serving, pour dressing over and toss thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: neiman marcus monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Place milk in a heavy-bottomed pan on low heat.
Stir occasionally until small bubbles appear around the edges of the pan and milk is just hot.
Do not boil. Remove from heat; let cool slightly.
Place yeast and scalded milk in a large bowl.
When yeast is dissolved, stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Add flour; beat well.
Cover and allow dough to rise to almost double.
This may take up to an hour depending on the temperature in your kitchen.
After dough has risen, turn out onto a lightly floured work surface.
Punch down and roll out to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut into 2 inch diamond-shaped pieces.
Dip each piece in melted butter.
Arrange in a 4 inch pie pan, 4 or 5 pieces overlapping per loaf.
Allow bread to rise for half an hour.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven and brush with more melted butter.

title: shirley fey's soul food seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in your own bottle to use to season foods that you would like to have spicy.
I use this to create most of my own foods.
Season to your own taste. If find this has worked for me and my family.

title: not too fattening stuffing
directions: Saute chopped onion in bouillon.
Add bread.
Combine parsley, celery and seasonings.
Add to bouillon.
Moisten with egg; add sliced mushrooms.
Makes four 1/2 cup or six 3/4 cup servings; 80 calories per serving.

title: dumplings (for chicken)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Add cold water, enough to hold together, a little at a time.
Roll dough on a board to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in 1-inch strips, then in 2-inch pieces.
Put on cookie sheet in refrigerator for 30 minutes or 2 to 3 hours, so it will dry out.
Bring broth to a boil, drop in dumplings and bring to a boil again; reduce to a simmer.
Cook, uncovered, 12 to 15 minutes.
Add deboned chicken.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Add dry orange jello to Cool Whip, then cottage cheese and stir well.
Fold in drained mandarin orange slices and pineapple. Place a few orange slices on top to garnish.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: hominy chili
directions: Drain
hominy.
Pour into casserole.
Pour chili over hominy. Chop onions and sprinkle on top of chili mix.
Pour cheese over all and put in oven about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients and add 1 beaten egg; then fold in 1 can fruit cocktail.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and top with 1 cup sifted brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add thinly sliced potatoes and chopped onion.
Stir to coat potatoes with butter.
Add milk and seasonings.
Sprinkle cheese and ham over top.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Lower heat to gently simmer for about 40 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato-spam casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, onions and Spam in casserole dish. Salt potatoes. Blend soup and milk.
Pour over mixture. Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash or paprika, then sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat chicken salad
directions: Heat oil on medium heat. Add nuts. Cook and stir until nuts are golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Cool. Drain chicken. Add all other ingredients; cool for 2 hours. Serve on greens. Sprinkle with nuts or mix in nuts and use on favorite bread. Makes about 6 servings.

title: beet relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and chill overnight.

title: peppermint cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugars; beat in eggs. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture. Fold in candy.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookie edges just begin to brown.

title: make freida happy ham thangs(ham and cream cheese rolls)
directions: Soften the cream cheese and beat on high speed until fluffy. Dry the ham slices by layering between paper towels.
Divide the cheese evenly between the ham slices, spreading to cover completely.
Place an onion on the long side of the ham and roll up like a jelly roll.
Repeat with each slice.
Cut into 8 equal pieces and secure with toothpicks.

title: old-time fried okra
directions: Wash and drain okra.
Cut off tips and stem ends.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir egg into okra.
Dredge okra in flour mixture.
Heat shortening in large skillet until hot.
Add okra and fry until brown and crisp.
Drain well.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients, blending in the butter with a pastry cutter.
Put half in bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; put over the flour mixture.
Put the other half of flour mixture on top of that.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken livers with wild rice
directions: Prepare the wild rice according to directions.
Salt and pepper livers, then roll in flour.
Brown in skillet with 1 stick of oleo.
When done, pour chicken livers over wild rice and serve. Pour butter you cooked chicken livers in over the rice.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, sugar and butter.
Place in Pyrex dish and bake 6 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: basic cookie dough
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour. Refrigerate dough.
Can roll out dough and use cookie cutters or add chips or candies and drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° until golden, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: plain muffin
directions: Grease muffin tin. Add all dry ingredients together. Make a well in center. Beat egg until light, add shortening and milk. Mix and pour liquid into well and stir until flour mixture is well moistened. Fill muffin pan about half full. Bake at 400° for 20 - 25 minutes.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in large microwavable bowl. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Roast or 3/4 power for 10 minutes.
Stir and continue cooking 5 or 6 minutes or until forms soft ball stage.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Fold in marshmallow cream.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spread in pan and chill.

title: orange-jello salad
directions: Cream Jell-O and cream cheese together.
Add water and blend. Add pineapple with juice.
When almost firm, fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: mom's sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make a sauce out of remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° uncovered.
If it gets too brown, cover with foil.
Taste for doneness.

title: tortilla chips
directions: Cut tortillas into quarters. Heat oil 350 degrees. Drop pieces into hot oil until crisp and light brown/golden. Drain on paper towels. Salt to taste. Enjoy.

title: graham cracker crisps
directions: Bring sugar and oleo to boil; cook some.
Pour over crackers that have been placed close together on aluminum foil cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Leave on rack to cool.

title: carrot roast
directions: Combine all ingredients together, making sure it is well blended.
Spray loaf pan.
Place mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: wower chocolate cake
directions: Sift together in an 8-inch square glass pan or enamel pan the flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and soda.
Then add vinegar, vanilla, water and oil.
Mix until smooth.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325° (glass pan) or 350° (enamel or stainless steel pan).

title: mom's tomato soup
directions: Wash and cut tomatoes.
Chop onions, celery, parsley and bay leaves.
Add to tomatoes, cooking until celery is tender.
Press through sieve or blender.
Rub flour and butter into a smooth paste, thinned with tomato juice.
Then add to boiling soup.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: quick slaw
directions: Mix all together, chill for 1 hour, ready to serve. Salt and pepper to taste. If too sweet, add a little white vinegar and re-mix.

title: baked chicken with sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° until tender.

title: jewel cheese cake
directions: Prepare filling.
Soften cream cheese in large bowl; beat until fluffy.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, orange and lemon peels and vanilla.
Add very slowly to cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in cream.
Turn into pastry lined pan.
Bake at 500° for 12 minutes.
Do not open oven door.
Reduce oven temperature to 200°. Bake cake 1 hour longer.
Remove from oven; cool on wire rack away from draft.
Cake will shrink slightly as it cools.
When cool, loosen cake from pan with spatula.
Remove side of pan. Chill cake.

title: jamaican beef stew
directions: Coat the beef cubes in the seasoned flour.
Melt butter with the oil and add the steak to brown.
Remove and keep the cubes warm.
Add the chili, onions, garlic and ginger to the pan and cook gently for 3 minutes.
Return the meat to the pan and stir with a spoon.
Cover and simmer for 3 1/2 hours.
Serve with plain boiled rice.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
You can also add tomatoes, cucumbers, meat and cheese, if desired.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Beat together eggs, mustard and milk.
Layer croutons, cheese, sausage, egg mixture and soup into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 333° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: easy egg and sausage puff
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate (does better if refrigerated overnight).
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole; pour mixture into casserole.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked italian chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line shallow baking pan with foil; coat with margarine.
Wash chicken pieces, sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt and roll in flour.
Bake for 1 hour, basting with melted margarine every 5 minutes for the last 20 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Let set for 3 hours the cucumbers, onions and salt.
Then drain and rinse.
Add sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed, alum and turmeric.
Bring to boil, put in jars, can and seal.

title: cheese and onion bread
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
In bowl, combine onion with egg, sour cream and pepper.
Mix well and set aside.
In another bowl, mix flour and baking powder.
Cut in 1/4 cup butter until crumbly and fine.
Stir in half of the cheese. Add milk to make soft dough.
Pat dough in a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Spread sour cream mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and parsley.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook sugar, butter and salt over medium heat until it comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook five minutes at a lower temperature, stirring occasionally.
Put popcorn in large container.
Pour sugar and butter mixture over popcorn.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread popcorn into two cookie sheets.
Bake for 1 hour in 250° oven.
Break apart and put in airtight container.

title: brownies
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool, then frost.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans about an hour.
Cook about 1 hour and then place all ingredients in a pan.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Cook about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until done.
Serve with crackers or corn bread.

title: sloppy joe hamburgers
directions: Brown hamburger in a skillet and drain off the fat.
Mix all ingredients together over a hot fire until boiling.
Put on warm hamburger buns.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese and corn chips.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Place meat in pan and add vegetables.
Mix salt, sugar and tapioca with tomato juice.
Pour over meat and vegetables and cover tightly.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Serves 12.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and wrap in foil.
Set in baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool, reserving liquid and dice chicken.
Mix liquid with soup and seasonings.
Heat and set aside.
Heat small amount of oil in skillet.
Dip each tortilla in oil until softened, then drain on paper towel.
Grease bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole and overlap 3 tortillas evenly in bottom.
Add 1/4 each of chicken, chilies, cheese, onions and soup mixture.
Repeat layers of tortillas and other ingredients until all are used.
Bake at 375° for approximately 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Cream together milk, Miracle Whip and sugar until creamy; mix well with cabbage and carrots.
Chill. Place on lettuce leaves.
Place pineapple chunks on and around and for color, grate a carrot and sprinkle on top.

title: zesty barbecued ribs(microwave)
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs; cut into serving pieces.
Place in 3-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Add onion.
Cover with casserole lid.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grind or grate first 6 ingredients.
Add salad oil, eggs and pepper.
Spread herb seasoned croutons on top and then some cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325°.
In pan over very low heat, melt chips with butter.
In large mixing bowl, beat chocolate mixture with remaining ingredients (except nuts) until smooth.
Stir in nuts, pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Good served warm with ice cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cook over medium heat until soft ball stage or 250° with a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add last 3 ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased pan.
Yields a 9 x 13-inch pan size.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook and brown the ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in mustard, evaporated milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook together until it thickens.
Add ketchup and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: sausage brunch
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight in 10 x 14-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fruity party punch
directions: Cook water and sugar until sugar dissolves, then boil 5 minutes.
Add frozen juices and Hawaiian Punch to sugar water and mix well.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serve cold. Makes 24 servings.

title: wienie roll-ups
directions: Cut wienies in half.
Mix corn meal mix and buttermilk in cup. Drop wienie halves into cornmeal mixture.
Spoon over wienies until well covered.
Take out and roll in dry cornmeal.
Fry until brown in hot oil.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt oleo and chips.
Cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Put coconut on wax paper.
Put mixture on coconut and roll up tight. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Slice into cookies.

title: sweet and sour apples and sausage dinner
directions: Saute apple in 2 tablespoons butter in skillet until tender. Remove from skillet.
Saute green pepper and scallions in butter remaining in skillet until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Saute sausages in skillet until browned.
Pour off drippings.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soda, in 4 to 5-quart microwave dish.
Cook on High for 12 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes.
Stir in the teaspoon of baking soda until mixture becomes foamy.
Continue cooking for 1 minute.
This creates the brown color.
Beat until mixture becomes tacky (about 1 minute). Drop by spoonfuls onto foil.

title: squash fritters
directions: Salt squash; let drain in colander.
Squeeze moisture from squash.
Combine all ingredients except oil in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Fry a small amount at a time in deep fat until brown on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix gelatin according to package directions and refrigerate until beginning to set.
Cut orange sections in halves.
Mix with sugar and combine with other ingredients.
Stir into gelatin. Refrigerate until jelled.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Butter and cocoa bottom of Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tofu salad
directions: Heat oil and add garlic.
Add shoyu and green onions.
Bring to boil and turn off.
In an 8 x 8-inch baking pan, slice tofu into cubes and lay in pan.
Layer onion, tomato, cucumber, watercress and tuna.
Pour sauce over it and refrigerate.

title: pork chops deluxe
directions: Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and ginger.
Brown chops slowly in heavy skillet. Arrange in single layer in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add butter to skillet drippings. Saute apple rings until slightly tender.
Place 1 ring on each chop.
Cover. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Place 1 cherry in center of each ring.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture. Baste with pan drippings to moisten sugar.
Increase oven temperature to 350°. Bake, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bran nut muffins
directions: Mix cereal and mix; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder and soda; set aside.
Mix egg with undrained pineapple and mashed banana.
Thoroughly combine all three mixtures; stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into 24 nonstick muffin cups sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in bottom of casserole.
Add sugar, spices and lemon juice.
Rub other ingredients together as for pie dough. Press over top of apples.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes in moderate (350°) oven.
Serve warm with cream or lemon sauce.

title: chinese barbecue pork
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put over pork loin and marinate overnight.
Place on broiler rack with water in bottom of broiler pan.
Have oven at 425°.
Bake 10 minutes. Turn, baste and bake 10 minutes more at 425°.
Turn heat to 350° for 30 minutes more.
Keep basting and turning.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice, sugar, salt and pineapple juice.
Chill until gelatin begins to set.
Combine cabbage with pineapple and fold into gelatin mixture.
Put in 4-cup mold which has been rinsed in cold water.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients. Add vanilla, chocolate chips and flour. Dough will not be very stiff. Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add the sugar, salt and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Pinch off about 2 tablespoons of dough for each pretzel.
Shape into traditional pretzel twists or other shape as desired.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Brush with egg; sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: southwestern corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into greased hot baking dish (iron works best).
Bake at 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with 1 tablespoon sugar; let stand 5 minutes.
Add egg, oil, salt, dry milk, 2 1/2 cups warm water and 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir in 2 cups flour; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
By hand, gradually beat in additional flour, enough to make a soft dough, mixing well after each addition so that dough is well blended.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover loosely with a light towel; let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except lettuce, and bacon bits.
Pour over shredded lettuce.
Top with bacon bits.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Mix peanuts and pretzels in chocolate.
Pour on wax paper to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: beef tacos
directions: Heat the oven to 225°.
Warm the taco shells in the heated oven.
Brown the beef in a frying pan.
Stir in the ground chiles, oregano, cumin, garlic and salt.
Cook until the flavors blend about 5 minutes.
Take the taco shells from the oven and raise the heat to 400°.
Fill the taco shells with the meat mixture.
Add cheese.
Heat in the oven until cheese melts, about 5 minutes. Top with lettuce, onion and tomato.
Serve with salsa.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add 1 egg at a time, stir after each egg is added.
Beat for 15 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured ten inch angel food or bundt cake pan for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Blend all of the ingredients and keep in the refrigerator; tastes better if made a day ahead.
Serve with toppings of croutons (toasted), chopped eggs, etc.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray nonstick vegetable spray in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour in corn and rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover for 20 to 25 minutes, until fork-tender.
Let cool to touch.
Peel and slice crosswise.
Place in casserole in overlapping rows.
Put the next 8 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Let marinate a few hours or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: caramel-filled chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat sugar, brown sugar and butter until fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs. Beat well. Add flour, cocoa and baking soda. Blend well. Stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
For each cookie, with floured hands, shape 1 tablespoon dough around 1 caramel, covering completely.
Combine remaining pecans and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Press one side of each ball into pecan mixture.
Place nut side up on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool on sheet for 2 minutes.

title: taco bake
directions: Spray baking pan with Pam.
Beat together flour, eggs and milk.
Spread in baking dish.
Set aside.
Saute onion in butter; add meat and brown.
Add taco seasoning, picante sauce and pinto beans.
Mix well.
Pour over bread mixture and top with cheese. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8 people and may be cut in half.

title: coconut or chocolate tarts
directions: In 2-cup glass measure, combine sugar, cornstarch and dash of salt.
Blend in milk.
Cook, uncovered, at High for 2 minutes until thickened, stirring after 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir a moderate amount of hot mixture into egg yolk; return to hot mixture.
Cook uncovered at High for 30 seconds until thickened, stirring once. Stir in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into tart shells.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 2 tarts.

title: classic popovers
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Butter six custard cups.
Combine flour and salt. Beat eggs and milk together and blend into flour until smooth.
Pour into cups and bake 30-35 minutes.
Run a knife around the cup edge to loosen. Cool 5 minutes, then remove.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Just before serving, drain salad.
Serves 6.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jalapeno black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and tuna dinner
directions: Cook macaroni and peas for 20 minutes; drain.
Cook onion, mustard and paprika in butter until onion is tender.
Add peas, tuna and macaroni.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and salt.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Stir in egg, cooled shortening and flour.
Use only enough flour to handle, using remaining on board to knead.
Put in greased bowl to rise.
