When dough has doubled in bulk, punch down and allow to rise until almost double in size once again.
Roll out dough to 1/3 inch thick.
Cut with floured 3-inch cutter.
Let rise on board until very light, 30 to 45 minutes.
Fry and drain on absorbent paper.
You put a glaze on them or icing.

title: vegetarian baked beans
directions: Place beans in baking dish.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in oven for 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: barbecued tandori chicken
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in blender and mix. Coat chicken with remaining seasonings and rub 2 to 3 tablespoons oil. Pour mixture from blender over chicken and marinate for 12 to 24 hours. Cook on grill, basting for sauce.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook over medium heat the vinegar, sugar and eggs until thick. Cool and add to Cool Whip; beat together.
Slice bananas in bottom of bowl.
Add mixture, then crushed peanuts.
Repeat until all mixture is used.
Crushed peanuts should be on top.

title: fireside crunch
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add brown sugar.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until thick and smooth, about 5 minutes.
Pour over popped corn and stir.
Stir occasionally as it cools.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix
sugar and eggs very well.	Then add margarine that is softened
at
room	temperature.
Add
nuts and flavoring. Beat well
by hand and pour into two unbaked pie crusts.
Bake slowly until the filling is done (about 45 minutes) at 325°.

title: grilled salmon with lime butter
directions: In shallow bowl, combine lime juice and ginger root; add salmon fillets and let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes, turning fillets over every 5 minutes.

title: coconut-sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions, making two 8 inch layers. When completely cool, split each layer, making four layers.

title: linguine salad
directions: Night Before:
follow directions on box of linguine to cook it.
Put it in a bowl and let it cool.
When cooled, add 1/2 bottle of Viva Italian.
Stir through and store overnight in the fridge.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Chop onion and hamburger and cook. Drain grease off. In separate bowl, mix corn meal, soda, salt, corn, milk, eggs and oil. Remove meat from skillet. Heat skillet and sprinkle with corn meal. Brown lightly. Do not stir. Pour in 1/2 batter. Place all the meat over the batter. Place cheese on top of meat. Cover with remaining batter and cook in oven 50 minutes; cool 30 minutes before eating.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add 3 cups hot water.
Add tomato paste. Stir in chili powder and onion.
Cover and simmer.
About 15 minutes before eating, add flour paste and kidney beans.
Stir a lot!

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese together.
Serve with fruit.
Can also be served with cookies.

title: peach or pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter or oleo in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Drain peaches or pineapple and arrange with cherries in sugar mixture.
Mix cake as directed; spread over fruit.
Bake at 350° until done (45 to 50 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes; turn upside-down onto large platter.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: quick fish
directions: Spice:
Roll fillets in Bisquick mix (mixed per instructions on box).
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with a twist of lemon on the side.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Beat eggs slightly with a fork; add other ingredients.
Spread mixture over cooked pastry.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Use fork to blend.
Mix well.
Put in greased muffin pan, 1/2 full, or make into biscuits. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add cold water to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened (consistency of unbeaten egg whites).

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Combine eggs and carrots with sugar mixture until well mixed. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Mix until moist.
Drop
from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: skillet zucchini
directions: Select large skillet, melt Crisco, dredge zucchini in flour, season with salt and pepper.
Cook zucchini until crispy tender. Add onion, cook only until tender, remove from heat, add tomatoes, serve hot.

title: bucket of mud
directions: Put
Oreo
cookies in blender to make crumbs.
Mix Oreo cookie crumbs,
margarine, softened cream cheese, pudding mix and milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in child's play sand bucket and serve with the shovel.
Kids love this.

title: tea bag slush
directions: Boil tea bags in 2 cups water and cool.
Boil sugar in 7 cups water and cool.
Mix all together and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon. Serve in glass with 1/2 slush mixture and 1/2 Team or 7-Up.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening until crumbly; reserve 1/2 cup.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Add sour milk and eggs; mix well. Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pans; top with reserved 1/2 cup crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: no-peek skillet chicken
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, heat oil and brown chicken.
Drain. Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms, garlic and soup mix.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is done. Serve over hot noodles. Yields 6 servings.

title: gooey butter coffeecake
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, margarine and 2 eggs.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mixture will be sticky.
Mix with mixer, cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over top of cake.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Center will still be wiggly.

title: pears in lite syrup
directions: Note:
Need 8 to 10 canning jars, rings and lids.

title: breakfast tomorrow
directions: Butter 11 x 9-inch glass pan.
Place cubes of bread in dish. Cover with cooked sausage.
Beat the eggs, half and half, salt and pepper, then pour over the sausage and bread.
Top with cheese. Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Mix and chill for several hours.
Combine parsley and pecans.
Shape salmon mixture into 8 x 2-inch log.
Roll in nuts and parsley. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Bring molasses, water and soda to a boil.
Pour over crumbs in pie dish.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Wash, trim and pare carrots.
Slice carrots 1/2-inch thick. In 1-quart casserole dish, combine carrots, water, butter, cinnamon, honey and pecans.
Cover; microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes, or until tender, stirring once.
Let stand covered.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and eggs.
Slice and place in layers in casserole dish.
Cook bacon.
Mix salt, bacon drippings, mustard, sugar, flour, vinegar, water and celery seed.
Boil until clear. Add celery and onion and let stand a few minutes.
Lastly add the mayonnaise and parsley; mix.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with bacon pieces.

title: almost pizza
directions: Place potatoes in greased 9 x 13 pan; set aside.
Brown beef; drain fat.	Combine cheese soup and milk in small saucepan; cook and stir until heated.
In mixing bowl, stir together tomato soup, onion, sugar and oregano.
Sprinkle ground beef over potatoes; put cheese mixture over the beef.
Top with the tomato soup mixture. Put on pepperoni and any other pizza topping you choose.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake in 375° oven 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: raspberry muffins(12 muffins or 1 loaf)
directions: In medium bowl, mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar. Make a well in the center and stir in eggs and oil.
Thoroughly mix in raspberries and stir in pecans.
Spoon into lightly greased muffin tins.
Muffin cups will be quite full.
Batter is heavy and will not overflow.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.
This recipe can also be baked in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Double the recipe to bake in a Bundt pan.

title: how to heat tv dinner
directions: Remove dinner from carton.
Place in microwave.
Follow heating instructions on box.

title: cheddar cheese ring with preserves
directions: Mix together and fill ring mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put strawberry preserves in center of ring.
Serve with Sunshine Krispy crackers.

title: saucy cocktail meat balls
directions: Shape into 50 small balls.
Broil in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan until browned (or cook in microwave).

title: brownies
directions: Cream cheese, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs gradually, beating thoroughly.
Add flour and cocoa; mix well.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch square pan in moderate oven for 35 minutes.
While still warm, cut into squares.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Use small pan; double everything if you use large pan.

title: old timey tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll thin and cut out.
Ingredients are estimated, as told to me, by the late Aunt Bessie Gillis Pigg.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: *You can find this in any Oriental market.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all well.
Will keep in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Dissolve
sugar
and
jello
in water; cool.
Cut slice from each end of orange;
chop fine.
Put cranberries and nuts through food
chopper.
Mix orange, cranberries and nuts with jello and chill.
I use food processor to chop cranberries and nuts.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Combine all ingredients except sauce; stuff shells with chicken mixture.
Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of baking dish.
Place desired number of shells open side down in single layer.
Cover with sauce (1/3 cup per 3 shells).
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes. Freeze remaining unsauced shells.

title: beefburger bar-be-que
directions: Brown meat in 12 inch skillet, drain off excess grease. Add next 6 ingredients, fill catsup bottle half full of water and shake. Add water to mixture, stir mixture well. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add more water if necessary, for desired consistency. Serve on hamburger buns, cooked rice or cooked pasta as desired. Yield 6 hearty portions or 10 small ones. This can be made to serve 40 for outdoor picnic. Use 15# hamburger, 5 onions, 6 peppers, 3/4 c. sugar, 6 bottles catsup, and water to desired consistency.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries and combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes and walnuts.
Fold in whipped cream; chill.
Serve in large bowl or individual lettuce cups.
Garnish with clusters of green and red grapes, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cocoa roll
directions: For the roll crust, put flour and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut Crisco into the flour.
Add the water, mix well.
Put the dough on a well floured surface.
Knead until thick enough to roll out. Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with butter until covered, sprinkle with cocoa.
Roll up into a single roll.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla, baking powder and flour.
Warm the milk and add the butter.
Add this to the batter (the batter will be thin).
Place in greased cookie sheet and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
After removing from oven, while hot, spread on peanut butter.
Refrigerate until cool and peanut butter firm.
Melt chocolate and spread on top of peanut butter.
Chill.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mixed well with loving words, so kind.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Hollow out a round loaf of rye bread.
Cube the insides and fill the hole with dip.
Put cubes around outside of loaf.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Prepare enough crust to line an oblong pan.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions on the package.
Cream the cheese and sugar together.
Fold in the Dream Whip.
Pour into the crust lined pan and cover with pie filling.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Mix the flour, soda, nutmeg, baking powder, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and salt with the sugar, eggs and lard.
Mixture will be stiff.
You will have to use hands.
Grease a 12 x 9-inch pan or a loaf pan.
Press in dough with the apples. Sprinkle a little cinnamon on top. As cake bakes the dough will rise up around the apples. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: nut roll
directions: Melt marshmallows and Eagle Brand milk together in top of double boiler. Cool. Place in large bowl and mix all ingredients together. Have a bowl of cold water set aside so you can wet hands and mix good. Roll out and it will keep for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: chicken breasts picante
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan. Flatten chicken breasts slightly. When the oil is hot, add the chicken and cook over high heat, turning once, until golden brown and white in the center, but still juicy, about 8 minutes on each side. While the chicken is cooking, cut the roasted red pepper into thin strips. Remove the cooked chicken from the pan. Pour off any excess oil. Add the wine and bring to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly to loosen any browned bits on the bottom of the pan. Add the red pepper strips. Stir in the capers without draining. Spoon the sauce over the chicken and serve to 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli
as directed on package and drain.
Cook rice. Mix
all ingredients together and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake in pan.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except whiskey, sugar and butter) in bowl.
Beat for about 2 minutes.
Bake in ungreased angel food pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Put carrots, pepper and onion in a bowl.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients, heat and stir until blended.
Pour hot sauce over vegetables.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: california vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together 1/2 stick margarine, cheese and vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Mix 1/2 stick margarine and Ritz crackers.
Pour over vegetables.
Place back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Roll pastry dough thin.
Spread chopped chicken, butter, salt and pepper over dough.
Cut, as if you were making jelly rolls, in 1-inch sections.
Place in pan.
Pour mixed vegetables, 2 cups of chicken broth and sage over chicken rolls.
Bake at 375°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until clear.
Add the Jell-O and cool.
Line a 9-inch baked crust with the cream cheese and sugar. Top with fresh whole strawberries to fill pie shell. Top with glaze and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Chill for a time in the refrigerator. Make into about 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
May roll balls in granulated sugar before baking.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix with fork until well blended.
Roll into 9-inch pie shell.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together eggs and ketchup.
Add hot water and envelope of onion soup; stir well, then add the bread and hamburg.
Pour into a bread pan.
Cook for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple and juices in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pie filling on top of pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Cut stick of margarine into thin slices and put on top of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: moist white cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans. Using electric mixer, cream butter until fluffy. Add sugar and continue to cream for 6 to 8 minutes. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and milk alternately to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour. Add vanilla and continue to beat until just mixed. Divide batter among prepared pans. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Invert cakes onto cooling racks. Cool completely and spread cake layers with your favorite frosting.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Mix 2 cups of flour with yeast.
Stir water, milk, butter, sugar and salt over low heat until butter melts.
Cool for about 5 minutes.
Add to the flour and yeast.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and make bite size balls; chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to set.

title: flan
directions: Melt sugar over stove in a large round heavy-duty baking pan or Flan pan.
Do not burn.
Coat pan completely, then set aside. Separate 8 eggs.
Combine egg yolks, sweetened condensed milk, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Pour into Flan pan with sugar. Combine cake mix, 2 eggs, water and sour cream.
Pour into egg mixture in Flan pan.
Do not mix up.
Place Flan pan in another bigger pan and fill at least an inch high with water.
Place in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove and flip over onto glass plate.

title: japanese spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until almost tender.
In meantime, mix all other ingredients together.
Add sugar to your taste and mix into spareribs and cook for additional hour or until done.

title: cranberry-applesauce
directions: Combine cranberries, apples, water and orange juice.
Bring to boil; turn heat down and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes until cranberries pop and apples are tender.
Add honey and orange rind. Puree in electric blender.
Serve warm or cold.
Yield:
about 3 cups.

title: skillet tomatoes and zucchini
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add zucchini and onion; cook over medium heat until crisp-tender.
Gently stir in tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until tomatoes are tender.
Remove from heat; sprinkle with cheese and croutons. Cover; let stand 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: rhubarb-strawberry crisp
directions: Cut rhubarb in 1-inch pieces. Add strawberries and sugar. Spread in a 9-inch square baking dish. Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter.
Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle crumb mixture over the rhubarb and strawberries. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until rhubarb is tender. Very good.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In large bowl, blend cake mix, sour cream, oil, sugar, water and eggs. Beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Pour 2/3 of the batter in a greased and floured tube pan. Sprinkle filling over batter. Spread remaining batter evenly over filling mixture. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly. Cool in pan for 25 minutes; then remove.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or done.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: split pea soup
directions: Heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion, carrot and celery; cook, stirring occasionally, 8 to 10 minutes or until softened. Add ham; cook stirring, until heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add water, broth, split peas, rosemary, thyme, bay leaf and pepper to onion.
Simmer 50 minutes or until peas are tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook pasta in pot of boiling water for 6 minutes; add broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook 2 minutes; drain.
Blend Ricotta, Mozzarella, oregano and red pepper seasoning in bowl.
Toss pasta and 1 cup sauce in pot.
Spoon half of pasta into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole or individual casseroles.
Spoon 2/3 cheese mixture over top.
Add remaining pasta.
Spoon on remaining sauce and top with cheese mixture.
Bake, covered, in preheated 450° oven for 25 minutes until heated.
Serve with grated Parmesan.

title: quick cheese sauce
directions: Over medium heat, melt cheese in a little hot milk on the stove.
Add rest of ingredients, then simmer until thickens.
Good over eggs and muffins for breakfast; good with broccoli, too.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Mix meal and salt in bowl.
Add water with butter.
Lastly add cracklins.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain and set aside.
Mix soup, eggs, mayonnaise and onion.
Add cheese and broccoli; mix well. Put into 2-quart casserole and top with cheese cracker crumbs. Cook, covered, for 20 minutes at 400°, uncover for about 5 minutes more.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add eggs, vanilla and salad oil and mix very slowly.
Add nuts and pears and mix in slowly.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan in 350° oven until golden brown, at least 1 1/2 hours.
Cool thoroughly before removing from pan.
This is a delicious and very moist cake.

title: gourmet stew
directions: Mix all ingredients except rice.
Cook in roaster at 325° for 3 hours, covered.
Serve over cooked rice or Chinese noodles. Serves 6.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Use with hot water, apple cider, apple juice or cranberry or cran-apple.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Stir in eggs, molasses and vinegar.
Sift and add remaining ingredients.
Mix ingredients until blended.
Form dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet about 12 minutes. As the ball melts down during baking, the cookie develops the characteristic crinkled surface.
When cool,
ice to taste.
A topping to delight the children is half a marshmallow, cut side down, on the almost baked cookies.
Return to oven about 4 minutes.
Makes about 10 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: hawaiian pork
directions: Beat egg in a medium bowl.
Add water, flour and salt until smooth.
Stir in meat, mixing until coated.
Melt shortening in medium skillet.
Add meat mixture; cook and stir until meat is brown.
Remove from heat; keep warm.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine chicken, water, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper in a 6-quart Dutch oven.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until the chicken is tender. Remove from heat.
Remove the chicken.
Skim the fat from the broth.
As soon as the chicken is cool enough to handle, remove the meat from the bones, chop and set aside.

title: ramen cole slaw
directions: Remove the small packet of seasoning from the package of Ramen Pride Oriental noodles.
Combine the oil, vinegar and packet of seasoning.
Combine cabbage, water chestnuts, almonds, sesame seed, salt and onion.
Pour dressing over the cabbage mixture. Before serving, crumble the dry Oriental noodles over top of the cabbage.

title: texas meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form meatballs, size optional. Place in 12 x 9-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake until done.

title: mayonnaise biscuits(perfect for dumplings)
directions: Sift flour into bowl.
Stir in mayo and add only enough water to make a moist dough.
Roll and cut into rounds if making biscuits.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Yield:
16 biscuits.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and eggs together in a pan. Boil potatoes 30 minutes or so; eggs, 10 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients, then eggs and potatoes when done.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate just before you serve.
Add Chinese noodles and serve.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies(no bake)
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes, then add rest of ingredients.
Put out by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and let set, may need to put in refrigerator for just a little while.

title: mimi's spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes.
When cool, ice with can of cream cheese frosting.

title: delicious apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg.
Add apples.
Put in pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pastry tube frosting
directions: Combine everything.
Mix on slow speed with hand mixer until smooth.
Do not beat.
Food coloring may be added for desired color.
Frosts a 9 x 13-inch cake or 24 cupcakes.

title: chicken barley soup
directions: In large kettle, cook chicken in water.
Cool broth and skim off
fat.
Bone
chicken and cut in bite size pieces and return to	kettle	with
remaining
ingredients.
Simmer
20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Mix vegetables with all the ingredients, except the crackers and margarine.
Pour mixture into a cooking dish and spread out evenly in the dish.

title: sangria
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Slice oranges, apples and lemons if desired and put in punch.
Chill.
Serve.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Divide the popcorn between 2 large bowls.
Oil 2 lipped cookie sheets very well and set aside.
In a deep saucepan, combine the brown sugar, corn syrup, butter, salt and cream of tartar.
Insert a candy thermometer.

Bring to a boil and cook the mixture over medium heat for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until syrup reaches 260° (hard ball stage). Remove from heat and quickly stir in the baking soda. The mixture foams up.

Pour the syrup over the popcorn, half in each bowl. Work quickly to coat all of the popcorn evenly with the caramel syrup. Spread popcorn evenly on the cookie sheets and bake for 1 hour, stirring 3 times. Remove from the oven and spread popcorn on waxed paper to cool, breaking up the larger pieces, if necessary. Store in airtight containers.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: beef boat dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve in hollowed out loaf of pumpernickel bread, French bread, etc.

title: pumpkin chocolate loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and oil. Add eggs; mix well. Stir in the pumpkin, melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well.

title: house of plenty turtle pie
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup chocolate chips and the pecans in pastry shell. Pour caramel topping over chips and pecans. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. In a saucepan over low heat, cook and stir cream and remaining chips until smooth. Gradually add to the cream cheese mixture. Mix well. Carefully spread into pastry shell. Yields 8 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts and coconut in pan evenly first.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Next melt margarine and mix with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spoon over mixutre and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: brussels sprouts parmesan
directions: Halve
any
large
Brussels sprouts.
In
a
quart microwave safe casserole combine sprouts and water.
Microcook covered
on
100% power (High) 3 to 5 minutes or until tender. Let stand, covered, while preparing garlic butter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli into dish you are going to use and thaw.

title: ice cream piegroves, texas
directions: Mix pudding and milk, add ice cream.
Put in cold baked pie crust.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
For topping, melt oleo and stir in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: wontons
directions: Mix all the above ingredients (except wrapper) together in a bowl. Place approximately 1 tsp. in the center of the square wonton wrapper. Fold diagonally and wet the two sides of the wrapper so you will have a triangle. Now wet the two sides of the triangle and connect, forming a crown. Deep fry wontons in oil at approximately 350° until golden brown. ZUCCHINI QUICHE

title: blueberry cupcakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternately add orange juice and flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in blueberries and orange rind.
Fill paper cups 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 cupcakes.

title: porcupine meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients and add 1/2 cup to first mixture.
Shape in a loaf and put in baking pan. Pour remaining liquid over meat loaf.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: cathy's bread and butter pickles
directions: Do not pare cucumbers.
Slice thin.
Add onions, peppers and salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Let melt thoroughly for three hours.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Boil one minute.
Simmer to keep hot while filling sterilized jars.
Leave 1/2-inch at top.
Cool on cake rack.
Makes 8 pints.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with oil.
Mix Parmesan cheese, Bisquick, Italian seasoning, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken.
Arrange skin side down.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.
Turn chicken.
Divide chili sauce among halves.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake until cheese melts, about 5 minutes longer. Makes six servings.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup water.
Beat egg whites together; add 2 cups warm water, sugar, salt, oil, yeast mixture and the 7 1/2 cups flour.
Place into a very large bowl as this will double in size.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Leave overnight in refrigerator.
To use, roll out.
Cut with large biscuit cutter and place on oiled baking sheet, 2 1/2 to 3 hours before baking at 375° for about 20 minutes.
This will keep well in the refrigerator for up to 5 days.

title: spinach-asparagus salad(with strawberry dressing)
directions: To make dressing:
Combine strawberries, orange juice, vinegar, oil, honey and salt in blender.
Pulse on and off. Dressing should be chunky.	Cover and refrigerate.	For each serving, measure 2 cups spinach onto each of four plates.
Top each with 1/4 of the asparagus spears and drizzle with about 1/3 cup dressing.
Sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. almonds.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: unbaked caramel cookies
directions: Mix in large saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add 3 3/8 or 4 ounce package instant butterscotch pudding mix and 3 1/2 cups quick rolled oats. Mix thoroughly.
Cool 15 minutes.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper lined tray.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cheese, which is to be sprinkled over top.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: In small bowl, combine the oatmeal, buttermilk and raisins. Let this soak for 1/2 hour to absorb the liquid.
In a medium bowl, mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and wheat germ.
In large bowl, cream together the margarine, brown sugar, egg and honey to this mixture.
Alternate adding dry ingredients and oatmeal mix to large bowl until just combined.
Bake in greased muffin cups at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: apple butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg, oats and apple butter.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture along with the milk.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Chill well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: diane's zingy apricot chicken
directions: Mix together the dressing, soup mix and apricot preserves. Season chicken breasts and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour dressing mixture over chicken. Place in oven which has been preheated to 350°. Cover pan and bake chicken for about 1 hour, turning once. This really is delicious.

title: john mott's irish coffee
directions: Place the brown sugar in the bottom of a glass Irish coffee mug.
Add the whiskey; stir until blended.
Fill the mug with the coffee until the mixture comes to 1/2 inch from the rim.
Mix carefully.
Whip the cream with the sugar in a medium size bowl until it barely forms peaks.
Lay dollops of the cream mixture on top of the coffee.
Sip the coffee through the cream.
Yields 1 serving.

title: family favorite apple pie
directions: Mix two recipes of Can't Fail Pie Crust.
Fill unbaked pie shell with sliced apples.
In a bowl, mix sugar, cinnamon and flour.
Pour evenly over the apples.
Then sprinkle vanilla over the mixture.
Then cut up margarine or butter over the top.
Cover with top crust and, with knife, make slits for air.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pork pie
directions: To hot cooked rice, add all ingredients except pork.
Layer rice mixture and pork.
Put crumbs over.
Bake at 350° until hot throughout.

title: hopping john
directions: Place peas in large kettle; add water to cover generously and soak overnight or cover.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes and let stand 2 hours.
Place ham hock, onion, red pepper and water to cover in saucepan.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add ham hock mixture with liquid to peas.
Cover and boil 45 minutes or until peas are tender.
Add more water as needed to keep peas juicy.
Add rice and salt; stir.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serve hot.
Sliced sweet onion or pepper relish can be served with Hopping John.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rhubarb cupcakes
directions: Bake in 325°
oven for 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 18 to 24 cupcakes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat shortening and butter 2 minutes or until creamy. Add sugar, beating 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs; beat just until yellow disappears. Add flour, soda, salt and cocoa; alternate with milk. Mix at low speed until blended. Stir in vanilla. Pour into a Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan for 15 minutes and then cool on wire rack. Spoon Chocolate Glaze over cake, if desired.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender or a quart jar with a tight lid.
Blend or shake until foamy.
Serves 6.

title: mexican cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix together all ingredients except tortillas and paprika to form paste.
Lay tortillas on a flat surface and spread mixture on them.
Roll up each tortilla and cut into 1-inch rounds.
Sprinkle with paprika or chili powder.
Chill and serve.

title: macaroni and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; cook macaroni.
Mix all ingredients (except cheese) well and then add cheese, cut up.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: apple and sweet potato casserole
directions: Place sweet potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Add apples; layer with marshmallows.
Mix sugar, salt, cinnamon and nuts. Sprinkle over marshmallows.
Mix cornstarch with 1/2 c. water until smooth; pour over all.
Dot with butter.
Cover.
May make several days ahead; cover tightly and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add chopped nuts and cranberry halves.
Combine together in measuring cup, adding enough water to equal 3/4 cup liquid, melted shortening, orange peel and orange juice.
Stir egg into liquid. Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients, stirring just enough to mix.
Place batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or two smaller pans if for gift giving, spreading evenly, but making the corner and sides a little higher than the center.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until done
(toothpick comes out of center clean).
Cool.
Slices best when chilled.

title: caramel pecan dream bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Mix the cake mix, butter and 1 egg in a bowl until crumbly. Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Blend the condensed milk, 1 egg and vanilla in a bowl. Stir in the pecans and chips. Pour over the cake mix, spreading to cover. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean. Yields 36 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Cut in flour, soda and tartar or baking powder.
Mix dry ingredients with moist ingredients.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.

title: crabmeat pie
directions: In a pie plate, spread cheese on bottom.
Sprinkle crabmeat on top of cream cheese; then onion.
Spread chili sauce on top. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Softened the cream cheese and mix other ingredients in it. Shape into a ball shape and put pecans over it. Refrigerate.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Place potatoes in a medium saucepan; add water to cover. Bring to a boil, and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside 1/2 cup of potatoes.
Place the remaining potatoes and 2 tablespoons of water in container of an electric blender, cover and process until smooth.
Set aside.

title: tempeh chili
directions: Saute tempeh, onion and green pepper in oil for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer together for 30 minutes or more.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream oleo with sugar. Blend flour and then add remaining ingredients. Pour into shallow unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk for 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°. Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients. Stir in shortening mixture, alternately with oatmeal and buttermilk.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers and stuff with the meat filling.
Place in saucepan and cover with soup and water mixture.
Cook on top of stove for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: old fashioned potato custard pie
directions: Wash potatoes; cut off ends.
Cut potatoes crosswise in pieces of about 2 inches.
Cook in boiling water until tender; drain off water.
Mash potatoes.
While hot, add butter first, then add the other ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into uncooked pie shell.
Bake for about 25 minutes at 375°.

title: easy brownies
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: polish crullers (krusciki)
directions: Blend first with a fork and add a little more flour as needed. Then mix with hands.
Roll out into a thin sheet (about the thickness of pie crust).
Cut into strips of approximately 5 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cut a slit about 2-inches long through the middle lengthwise.
Pull one end through the slit.
Lay the cruller flat on the work surface.
After you complete all of them, the crullers are ready for deep frying.
Frying is best if done in hot Crisco (not oil) in a large frying pan rather than a deep fryer.
Fry several at a time until golden brown as desired.
Lift out gently with tongs and let cool before serving.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: ham delight rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spread generously on each roll. Put 1 piece ham and 1 small slice Swiss cheese in each roll. Replace in pan the rolls came in.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: sausage stew
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Peel and dice 1 small onion.
Put onion in pan with 1 large tablespoon of butter and fry until brown.
Then add diced potatoes and cover with water.
Cook until soft.

title: pizza roll
directions: Sprinkle flour on bread board and roll out bread as thin as possible. Brush flattened bread with olive oil. Sprinkle with garlic salt, oregano and black pepper.
Alternate 4 slices ham, 5 slices Provolone cheese, 8 slices pepperoni, 4 slices Mozzarella cheese and 10 slices salami. Roll up as tight as possible.
Tuck ends under.
You may have to cut rolls in half.
Make sure the ends are tucked in. Brush roll with olive oil and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Brush pan with Wesson oil.
Place rolls in preheated oven and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: no roll sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugars and oleo until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight for easier handling.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes or until set, but not browned.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet. Yield: 9 to 10 dozen.

title: teriyaki potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; cut tiny new potatoes into quarters or medium potatoes into 1-inch pieces.
Melt butter and all seasonings together; toss with potatoes until covered.
Stir twice during cooking.
These can be microwaved, baked in the oven or grilled.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cream the cream cheese with the sugar.
Add milk and mix well. Combine with the thawed topping.
Remove the brown crumbs from angel food cake.
Break or cut cake into small pieces.
Mix cake with the creamed mixture.
Swirl cherry pie filling into cake mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish or serve from a pretty crystal bowl.
Will keep for several days in refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt in a large mixing bowl. Set aside.
Melt 2 sticks of margarine.
Stir in the cocoa and water; heat (to almost a boil) slightly.
While this is heating (1 minute in microwave), combine the last 4 ingredients.
When the heated mixture is done, pour and stir it into the flour mixture. Add the egg mixture.
Stir well and pour in a greased 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine gelatin, cornstarch and sugar.
Add cold water slowly and mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens slightly and becomes clear.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Cool until thick and lukewarm.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Drain all beans and mix together all ingredients; let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: miss bessie's baked cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Thin slightly with milk (like sweet potato pie filling).
Pour in greased baking dish.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: In bottom of casserole dish, place potatoes, then carrots and onion.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over.
Sprinkle on the cheese.
Crumble raw hamburger on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: shoe peg casserole
directions: Mix first eight ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix crackers and butter and put on top of mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating well.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (8 or 9-inch) cake layer pans, lined on bottom with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost tops only with Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: spiced winter fruit
directions: Arrange fruit in layers in ungreased 3-quart baking dish.
In a small saucepan, cook applesauce, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in sherry and spices.
Dot with butter and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: one egg cake
directions: Sift together in bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add the shortening, milk and vanilla; beat vigorously with spoon for 2 minutes, or mix with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Add the egg; continue beating for 2 more minutes.
Pour batter into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spud dog casserole
directions: If using instant potatoes, use directions on package.
Place hot dogs in greased casserole dish.
Cover with cheese slices, then put mashed potatoes on.
Top with bacon slices.
Cook in a 350° oven until bacon is crisp and potatoes are bubbly.

title: mama's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and cool.
Peel potatoes; cut into small chunks.
Separate egg yolks from egg whites.
Set yolks aside.
Chop whites and add to potatoes with onion.
In a small bowl, mash yolks.
Stir in mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Toss well. Adjust seasoning, if necessary.

title: lemon pepper chicken strips
directions: Place margarine in a Teflon pan and set aside. Sprinkle chicken with lemon pepper. Place in pan and add as much onion as desired. Cook on medium-high heat until brown on each side.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Boil margarine, sugar and syrup for 1 to 2 minutes. Add Eagle Brand milk. Mix well. Keep warm in crock-pot. Store leftovers in refrigerator. Also good on ice cream.

title: p d q fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in saucepan; remove from heat. Add confectioners sugar; beat well.
Pour into an 8 x 9-inch nonstick pan.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: broccoli, rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix rice and broccoli with soup and onion.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: applesauce oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine oats, flour and baking powder.
In another bowl, combine milk, applesauce and egg whites.
Add to dry ingredients. Mix well. Good with applesauce and cinnamon.
Diabetic Exchange: 1 starch/bread (2 pancakes).

title: biscuits(low salt, low cholesterol)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add oil to water and stir into dry ingredients with fork until thoroughly moistened.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crumble cake in bowl or container.
Mix pudding according to box and pour over cake.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream together; put on top of pudding mixture.
Combine strawberries and glaze together, then put on top and chill.

title: green bean salad
directions: Steam beans in a large frying pan with 1/4 inch of water (do not overcook, leave them slightly crisp).	Toss in the mixture at least one hour before serving.
Serve cool to room temperature. Salad keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate, butterscotch and peanut butter in microwave or double boiler.
Stir in pecans and potato sticks.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Chill until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Combine and add the next 6 ingredients; then add zucchini and well drained pineapple.
Mix well and add 1 cup chopped nuts, and 1 cup raisins (optional). Divide into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ten day slaw
directions: Chop and mix first 4 ingredients.
Add sugar.
Mix vinegar and oil and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables and chill.
Stir occasionally to coat.
Pimento can be added for color, if desired. Do not add carrots as they will bleed after a day.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour; saute in butter until golden brown. Mix soup, onions and seasonings in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour Minute rice into a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Stir all except 1/3 cup of soup mixture into rice.
Top with chicken.
Pour on remaining soup mixture.
Cover and bake 30 minutes in 375° oven or until chicken is tender.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix sugar, wheat flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add box of Raisin Bran.
Mix.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(May store the unused mixture in fridge for 6 weeks.)

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown
sausage	and
onion and drain
grease.
Add
all ingredients into a small casserole dish and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a greased casserole dish.
Mix cheese, sour cream, soup and 3/4 stick softened margarine and spread on top of potatoes.
Mix slightly crushed cornflakes with 3/4 stick margarine (melted) and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Make crumbs with listed ingredients.
Pour liquid in unbaked pie crust; put crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken in a large pot filled with water half the depth of the pot.
Chop carrots, celery and onion in large pieces. Saute together with butter and pinch of salt and pepper until light brown.
When chicken is finished, pull all meat off and discard bones.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except noodles, and boil for 30 minutes.
Add noodles boil 15 more minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all items except cheese and chips.
Pour into casserole. Top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; gently stir in berries.
Turn into pastry-lined pie plate; dot with butter.
Arrange lattice top, trim ends.
Seal and flute, building high edge.
Brush pastry with milk, sprinkle with sugar.
Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent over browning.
Remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
If 6 ounce box of Minute wild rice is used, prepare it according to package instructions and then proceed to add remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil 1 1/2 cups of water.
Add frozen broccoli; bring to boil again.
Add stick of oleo and diced onion.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups of Minute rice.
Stir and let stand 5 minutes.
Add cheese and celery soup.
Put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: sandpiper spinach salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high for 1 minute. Makes 1 pint.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Mix together and pour in baking dish. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rolled chicken washington
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Pound 1/4-inch thick with meat mallet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Spoon Cheddar Filling onto chicken; roll to enclose filling.
Sprinkle chicken rolls with flour.
Dip in egg; coat with bread crumbs.
Chill, covered, for 1 hour.
Deep fry rolls in 375° oil for 5 minutes or until crisp and golden brown; drain.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Yield:
6 servings.

title: sugarless pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine 1/2 of the Cool Whip with pudding, pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice. Pour into pie crust. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Quick chill in freezer 10 minutes, then refrigerate until firm.

title: easy chocolate chex mix
directions: Melt chocolate in dish in 200° oven, no hotter or will burn (will scorch very easy in microwave).
Stir occasionally.
Combine all dry ingredients in large container.
Pour melted chocolate over all; stir until covered good.
Spread on waxed paper until dry. Break up and store in containers.
Great at Christmastime.

title: sukiyaki(japan)
directions: Slice meat paper thin into 3 or 4-inch long pieces.
Brown in bacon grease.
Mix together soy sauce, sugar and water.
Add to meat.
Reduce temperature; cook until tender, about 30 or 40 minutes.
Place vegetables on top of meat; mix together.
Add Accent according to directions on container.
Cook 5 minutes, covered.
Add green onions; toss with meat mixture for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Serve over steamed rice.
Top with broken pieces of watercress (optional).
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses together with the Worcestershire sauce and chopped onion.
Mix well.
Mix by hand; shape into ball.
Roll ball into nut meats.
Place into a nice bowl.
Makes 12 servings.

title: silly putty
directions: Use 2 parts glue to 1 part liquid cornstarch.
Pour starch into glue a little at a time and mix.
Add more starch if needed so mixture is not sticky.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: crusty fried fish
directions: Salt, pepper and paprika the fish well.
Dip fish in the egg, lemon juice and water mixture.
Dip in finely crushed crumbs. Fry in oil until crisp and brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms & trim ends and pull stems out of mushrooms. Set stems aside.
Make a nice pocket in mushroom for stuffing to fit.
Place mushrooms in baking dish.
For the stuffing, take the mushroom stems and chop them up.
Place in medium pan.
Chop the crabmeat and scallions and place in same pan.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 c. butter and saute the mixture.
While sauteing add the above seasonings to taste.
(I have never measured anything for this recipe.)
Saute mixture for about 15-20 minutes.
Spoon mixture into each mushroom.
If there is any left just spoon it next to the mushrooms, it is good that way too.
Put several pats of butter in the baking dish before placing the pan in the oven.
Bake mushrooms at 350° for 1/2 hour.
After they have baked for 1/2 hour place a small amount of cheese on each mushroom and bake an additional 15 minutes.
(Put some cheese on the extra stuffing too.)

title: baked salmon
directions: Remove bones from salmon.
Add rest of ingredients in order given.
Add enough milk to make mixture soupy.
Pour into 2-quart casserole; top with pats of margarine.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for about an hour.

title: date cake
directions: Cover dates with boiling water; cool to lukewarm.
Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add date mixture, then sifted dry ingredients; beat well.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in waxed paper lined 8-inch square cake pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: nedra's avocado bean dip
directions: Step 1:
Spread beans in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
In a small bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour hot water on top.
Do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes until center is almost set.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Spoon sauce from bottom over top when serving.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: mexi-chili casserole
directions: Reserve 1 cup of the chips and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Combine remaining chips and cheese with the chili, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and onion (green pepper if desired).
Pour into 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Spread top with sour cream; sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Ring remaining corn chips around edge.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and pineapple.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: baked chicken with potatoes
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
Place chicken in large casserole dish, seasoning it well.
Brown on all sides.
Peel potatoes and slice; season with salt, pepper, garlic and onion powder.
When chicken is brown, remove chicken and place potatoes in dish.
Brown well in 350° oven.
Return chicken to dish with potatoes and cover with foil.
Bake about 25 minutes more.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature, then beat.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Add sugar and blend.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup hot water and mix in cheese mixture with nuts and 7-Up. Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown beef and onions in skillet; drain off drippings.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer and stir occasionally.

title: hot wings
directions: Cut up and wash wings.
Cover with oven fry and salt and pepper as desired.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes or until done.
In a medium saucepan, mix hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, liquid smoke and butter.
After wings are done, place in crock-pot on low heat.
Add hot sauce mixture and gently shake up.
Ready to serve.

title: apple-cheese sausage bake
directions: Pat sausage into an oblong pan about 1/2-inch thick.
If you use waxed paper the job is much easier.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pat stuffing mixture on sausage and roll up like a jelly roll.
Place roll in a shallow pan on a roasting rack.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spicy glazed chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine soup mix, dressing and preserves. (Makes about 2 1/4 cups.)
Pour half the glaze over chicken in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven, basting occasionally, 1 hour or until tender.

title: carrot and cabbage salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in warm water.
Add vinegar and salt.
Chill. When slightly thickened, fold in carrots and cabbage.
Turn into individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on crisp lettuce. Garnish with mayonnaise.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poor boy casserole supper
directions: Combine the beef, vegetables and bread crumbs, then add the egg, salt and pepper and mix until well blended.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown in the shortening over medium heat.

title: frost on the pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter for 1 minute.
Add granulated sugar and brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg, pumpkin and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture; mix until well blended.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Transfer to wire rack to finish cooling.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
(Recipe follows.)

title: all-in-one pound cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer for 20 minutes.
Pour mixture into well buttered and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes (until golden brown).

title: chocolate ribbon coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 cup of the coconut evenly in a shallow pan.
Toast 7 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, sugar and salt.
Add melted margarine.
Beat eggs and milk well.	Pour over corn mixture and mix well.
Put in casserole dish and bake 45 minute at 350°.

title: honey oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together and spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Combine.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 1 hour.

title: ham loaf
directions: Spread brown sugar over bottom of loaf pan, then sprinkle cloves over brown sugar.
Combine meat, bread crumbs, milk, eggs, mustard and salt and pepper with hands.
Pack into loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 375°.
Invert to serve.

title: taco pie
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco sauce; simmer for 5 minutes.
Open crescent rolls and flatten into the bottom and sides of a 2-quart casserole to form a crust.
Spread half of the crushed corn chips over crust.
Pour meat mixture into casserole.
Spread sour cream over meat mixture.
Top with remaining corn chips and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until crust is golden brown and cheese is melted. Serve topped with lettuce, tomatoes and green onions.

title: our favorite badger rose bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Add instant pudding.
Add whole bottle red food coloring; mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round layer pans.
Bake according to box directions or until toothpick comes out clean.
Top with favorite frosting or whipped topping.

title: chocolate-covered surprise cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine sugar and butter.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed.
Add remaining ingredients except cherries.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheets.
Press cherry half into center of each cookie.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Cool completely.
Frost cherry on each cookie.
Refrigerate until set.
Store tightly covered.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Pour over gelatin and cool. Add large can of drained crushed pineapple and the cranberries that have beef ground.
Add rind of 1 orange and pour into mold. Nuts and marshmallows may be added if desired.
Great salad for the holidays.

title: day ahead chicken casserole
directions: Mix bread stuffing, margarine
and
chicken broth.
Put half of mixture in bottom of 13 x
x 2-inch baking dish and press in place.
Mix chicken
and
remainder
of
stuffing mix with onion, celery, mayonnaise and
green
onions
and	spread over mixture in pan.
Beat eggs and
milk
and
pour over contents in pan.	Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until beans are no longer runny.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix liquid ingredients together. Combine dry and liquid ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Add flour and stir over medium heat. Add milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
In a casserole dish, place 1 can Veg-All, 1/2 cheese sauce and repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken with celery and bay leaf.
Cook broccoli a little.
Spray Pam in bottom of dish.
Layer broccoli and chicken soup on top of chicken.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese, bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour oxtails
directions: Brown oxtails well in lightly oiled skillet.
Pour off drippings.
Add water, wine, bouillon cubes, soy sauce and salt. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Separate onion into layers.
Saute onion and green pepper lightly in oil, set aside.
Mix cornstarch and brown sugar thoroughly, add to oxtails.
Cook, stirring, until thickens and clears.
Stir in vinegar, onion and green pepper.

title: swedish raspberry shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl combine cake mix, nuts, butter and egg.
Mix at low speed until crumbly.
Press mixture in bottom of pan.
Spread with preserves.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.

title: prosciutto and pea sauce
directions: Place cream in small saucepan and cook until it thickens and reduces by a third (10 minutes).
In skillet, heat oil and saute shallot (1 minute).
Add Prosciutto and cook 1 minute or longer. Add cream, sun-dried tomatoes and peas.
Cook 2 minutes or longer. Season with salt and pepper.

title: liver loaf
directions: Fry pork, remove from pan, add liver.
Sear on both sides. Grind pork and liver.
Pour water over cracker crumbs and combine all ingredients.
Dot with butter and bake (375°) for 40 minutes. Serves 4.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook beef and sausage and onion well. Drain grease. Stir in cheese until melted. Arrange bread on cookie sheet. Place alot of mixture on each slice. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned lemon pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar, salt and cornstarch in a medium saucepan.
Add water and cook until thickened, stirring almost constantly, about 10 minutes.
Stir some hot mixture into beaten egg yolks; return to saucepan and cook slowly 1 or 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add butter, lemon juice and peel.
Strain into pastry shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 10 minutes.

title: fanny mae fudge
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar and stir.
Add milk.
Stir until fairly warm and add marshmallows.
Bring to slight boil and shut off.
"Shave" the chocolate and add to above mixture.
Stir until chocolate is melted and thoroughly mixed.
Add walnuts and stir. Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: coconut custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° until firm.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Melt and blend first 3 ingredients.
Add cereal and mix well. Press in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Mix together in a bowl and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour (until cabbage is tender).
Stir occasionally. Makes 5 to 6 servings.
This recipe can be cooled and put into the freezer.

title: stuffed shells with broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Prepare pasta according to package directions. Set aside. In bowl, mix broccoli, Ricotta, Swiss cheese, salt and pepper. Pour 1 cup tomatoes in 13 x 9 x 2-inches baking dish, breaking up tomatoes with fork. Put 1 tablespoon cheese mixture into each shell and place open side up in pan. Pour remaining tomatoes over shells. Cover with foil and bake until heated through, about 25 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Stir in taco seasoning and water. Cook and stir until thickened. Set aside. Place chips in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook until smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in tomato juice.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir milk and bouillon into tomato mixture.
Heat rapidly to serving temperature.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jello fruit salad low calorie
directions: Mix jello according to package directions, reducing water to 1/2 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Let set until firm. Cut into small squares.
Stir in drained fruit.
Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese and fruit cocktail.

title: layer cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients to make a crust.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1 1/2 cups chopped walnuts over top of crust. Sprinkle coconut to cover nuts.
Add 1 bag chocolate chips over top of coconut.
Pour 1 can sweetened condensed milk over top of chips.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until milk starts to look brown.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Pour over Rice Chex.
Stir gently until coated.
Put powdered sugar in a bag and shake coated Chex until covered with sugar.
Put on cookie sheet.
Some may need separating.
Good refreshment item!

title: honolulu punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice and ginger ale according to quantity desired.
Tint with maraschino juice or grenadine.
Pour over crushed ice.

title: inside-out ravioli
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Add spinach liquid, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and paste and salt to meat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine macaroni, cheese, bread crumbs, eggs and oil.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni not quite done.
Drain.
In a pan melt margarine. Add flour and dissolve in the margarine, then add milk and some of the grated cheese (save some for top of macaroni).
Spray baking dish and put cooked macaroni in dish; pour sauce over and top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Place chickens in a large pot or Dutch oven.
Sprinkle chickens, inside and out, with salt and pepper.
Add water.
Bring to boiling.
Cover and cook for 50 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Remove chickens to serving platter.
Cut into serving portions.
Keep chicken warm while dumplings cook.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt the hershey bars, marshmallows and water in a double boiler; Heat until melted. Let mixture cool. Add cool whip and pour into crusts. Chill in ice box. Makes 2 pies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients and pour in a tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Zucchini bread may be frozen for later use.

title: elfo's special
directions: Cook spaghetti 10 minutes.
Stir.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water and set aside.
In a vegetable pot, heat butter, garlic clove (minced), garlic powder, shrimp and mushrooms.
Cook slowly in butter for 5 minutes.
Add spaghetti.
Sprinkle Romano cheese, salt, pepper and m.s.g.
Stir until hot without browning butter. Serve with fresh cheese on top.

title: chocolate cherry lust
directions: In saucepan, melt 1/2 cup chocolate chips with 1 tablespoon margarine, stirring frequently.
Pour chocolate onto a sheet of foil; spread evenly.
Refrigerate (will make chocolate curls).

title: microwave everyday meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine beaten eggs, milk, fine dry bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, sage and pepper.
Mix well.
Add ground beef; combine thoroughly.
In 9-inch glass pie plate, shape mixture into a ring, about 1-inch high around a small juice glass, having 2-inches at least in diameter.
Micro-cook, covered until meat is done, about 12 to 13 minutes, giving dish 1 quarter turn every 3 minutes.
Remove glass and let meat loaf stand 5 minutes before serving.
If desired, garnish with ketchup.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: unusual corn casserole
directions: Beat egg.
In following order, stir in sour cream, melted butter, cream-style corn, kernel corn and corn muffin mix.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: light chicken divan
directions: Brown the chicken in oil until done, about 5 minutes.
Add the broccoli, water, wine and soup.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Store in large covered container.
Add miniature marshmallows, if desired.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Cut up chicken or
use only dark or light meat.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Put
in
dry
iron skillet on simmer. Cook 15 minutes, covered; turn once.
Mix soy sauce and sugar. Take lid off and
pour
soy sauce mixture over chicken.
Cook, turning often, until done, about 45 minutes.

title: creamy fudge(makes about 3 pounds)
directions: In heavy saucepan, over medium heat, melt candy coating and margarine with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 9 or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Chill 3 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store tightly covered at room temperature or in refrigerator.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain.
Saute onion in margarine in skillet.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Mix well. Simmer for several minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine broccoli, sauce and rice in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can easily be doubled.
I do not double the cheese, though.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix all.
Let rise only once.
Make into rolls.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cook onion flakes and bacon until bacon is crisp.
Add green beans, sugar and vinegar.
Heat until hot; serve.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chili stuffed potatoes
directions: Pierce potatoes, microwave 16 minutes, rotating halfway through.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in corn, tomatoes, ketchup, pepper and chili powder.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Slit potatoes in half; spoon 1 cup meat mixture over potatoes.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a small square pan, arrange in layer as listed.
Serve with crisp tortilla chips.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Grease a 10 x 7-inch oblong pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti	until
tender and drain.
Brown meat in hot oil.
Add onions,
garlic,	celery	and peppers.
Also add tomato paste
and	water.	Simmer 10 minutes.
Add soda during simmering period.
Mix spaghetti and sauce.
Pour into a large baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Prepare 2 to 4 servings instant rice.
Melt cheese and add enough milk to make a creamy sauce.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: good dieter chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Heat oven to 400°.
Place chicken into baking dish or pan, skin side up, after putting salt and pepper on both sides.
Sprinkle until covered with paprika.
Bake until done about 30 minutes.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put sugar and butter in mixing bowl. Beat on medium speed until fluffy.
Stop once in a while to scrape the sides of the bowl.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
The dough won't be smooth until flour is added.
On low speed, add flour.
Mix until dough is smooth.
Scoop out a teaspoon of dough and put it on a cookie sheet.
Space cookies about 1-inch apart.
Bake until cookies are golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cookies cool completely before taking them off the cookie sheet.

title: easy crock-pot beef stew in wine
directions: Add all ingredients to the crock-pot; mix and cook on low all day.
Serve with noodles.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients, raisins, pecans and applesauce.
Fill muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers together. Cover with salt and allow to stand overnight.
Drain.
Add hot peppers, vinegar, spices (tied in cheesecloth) and sugar.
Boil until tender (approximately 15 minutes).
Pack in pint jars.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix together and cook until thick.
Beat 1 pint whipping cream. Beat egg whites.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.

title: peanutty sweet potatoes
directions: Cut baked sweet potatoes in half and spoon out the majority of the potato.
Leave the shells in place.
Mash potato pulp thoroughly until smooth.
Add peanut butter, milk and seasonings. Beat until well mixed and fluffy.
Refill shells with mixture and broil slightly before serving.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
Boil eggs.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Add eggs and pickles.
In a separate bowl, mix other ingredients.
When sugar is dissolved, add to potatoes.
Mix well and enjoy.

title: banana and blueberry pie
directions: Beat all of the ingredients (except bananas) with mixer until fluffy.
Then whip 1 pint whipping cream and 4 tablespoons sugar until thick enough to eat.
Add the ingredients to whipped cream. Stir until mixed and smooth.
Pour into the 2 graham cracker crusts lined with bananas.
Chill.
When ready to serve, pour 1/2 can Lucky Leaf blueberry pie filling (chilled) on each pie and serve. Delicious (keep in refrigerator).

title: tangy cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower in pieces and
cook in water for 5 minutes or until tender.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix mayonnaise, onion and mustard.
Pour over cauliflower. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Yields 6 servings.

title: farmer's seafood boil
directions: Boil a gallon of water, crab boil and salt.
Add potatoes, boil 10 minutes longer.
Then add your onions and sausage; boil 5 minutes longer.
Then add shrimp and corn and boil 5 more minutes. Drain and serve.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut chicken in strips 1-inch long.
Place in oiled skillet along with green peppers, onions, salt and pepper.
Saute until chicken is cooked and onions are golden brown.
Put fajitas in a 200° oven for 1 minute.
Remove and place some of the chicken mixture on each.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on each.
Roll fajitas and place, seam side down, in pan in one layer.
Place pan in oven for 2 minutes, then eat.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash ten minutes in salted water, drain.
Mash squash. Add sour cream, soup, carrots and onions; mix well.
Melt margarine and bread crumbs; stir well.
Layer squash mixture and bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: egg substitutes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend on lowest speed until mixed.
Store in refrigerator.

title: elegant blackberry
directions: Drain blackberries, reserving syrup.
Add water to reserved syrup to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil.
In meantime, soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add to hot syrup and water mixture, stirring until gelatin has dissolved.
Add ice cream and lemonade, blending well.
Fold in blackberries; turn into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold on plate and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo.
Sprinkle rice in pan.
Lay chicken on top. Sprinkle onion soup over this.
Add water.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Scald milk; add the remaining 2 cups water and salt and cool until lukewarm.
To this, add dissolved yeast and sugar.
Add 1/2 the flour and beat thoroughly.
Add melted shortening, then remainder of flour gradually and beat thoroughly after each addition.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic. Place in bowl, cover and allow to rise in warm place at 80° to 85° until double in bulk, about 2 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Let stand for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Make shallow cut on one side of meat.
Combine egg water stir in bread, cheese, onions, parsley, salt and pepper.

title: bill's cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs, 2 teaspoons vanilla extract and 3/4 cup sugar in mixer.
Pour into crust.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator for 3 hours.

title: frozen fruit pops
directions: In a blender container combine the bananas, juice concentrate and water.
Cover and blend until smooth.
