Pour mixture into 10 (3 ounce) paper cups or frozen pop molds.
Cover with aluminum foil and freeze one hour; insert stick into each cup through foil. Return to freezer for 3 to 5 hours, until firm, or overnight.
To serve, tear off paper or remove from mold.
Makes 10 pops.

title: zucchini slices(apple pie)
directions: Cut as for pie dough (reserve 1/2 cup for filling).
Place half of crust mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down; bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: sister's punch
directions: Boil water and	sugar
until sugar dissolves.
Then mix in gelatin.
Add juices.
Mix	well.
(This
may
be frozen to keep.) When ready to serve,
add
quarts
of ginger ale and ice.
(You may use more ginger ale, if you like.)

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add mashed bananas, and beat well. Mix
eggs, flour, soda, and 1 tablespoon water.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Mix.
Turn into well greased pan and cook at 350°.	If a large pan is used, bake 1 1/2 hours.
Bake 1 hour for 2 small pans.
Delicious if toasted in oven as well as eaten cold.
Freezes nicely.

title: old-fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add one egg at a time, beating one minute after each addition.
Sift cake flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add milk and vanilla to creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 thin layers.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, sour cream, pepper, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole, cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 more minutes.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well. Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: punch
directions: Stir all ingredients together and add 1 large can pineapple juice and 1/2 can of a medium frozen lemonade.
Put in refrigerator. May be put in freezer and shaken often to get slushy.
Serves 12.

title: breakfast casserole(for 10 servings)
directions: Cut crust off bread.
Arrange in bottom of 2-quart casserole. Cut remaining bread into into 1/4 squares.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese, ham, Parmesan and green onion over crust pieces.
Arrange bread squares over ham/cheese layer.
Combine remaining 4 ingredients; pour over bread and cheese layers.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Cake:
Add cake mix, flour, dry jello, oil and water.
Mix well and add 4 eggs, one at a time.
Stir well, then place in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy-does-it doughnuts
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, egg and melted shortening.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt, then add to liquid mixture.
Drop by teaspoon into shortening heated to 365°.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Fry all doughnuts to same degree of brownness.
Drain on paper towels. You can roll in confectioners or granulated sugar.

title: chicken thigh relleno
directions: Clean and invert the skin backward up to the end of the bone. Clean under running water.
Cut off the bones.
Separate the meat. Set aside the skin.

title: chili con carne
directions: Spray 10-inch skillet with nonfat cooking spray.
Set over moderate heat for 30 seconds.
Add ground beef and chicken.
Stir often until no longer pink (4 to 5 minutes).
Push to one side of the skillet.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook beef and onion until brown; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Spread in plate.
Top with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth (15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.
Can serve with sour cream, tomatoes, lettuce, shredded cheese and black olives.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, except sugar, and set aside. Beat eggs well, then add sugar and oil.
Beat well.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured loaf pan.

title: chicken a la nora
directions: Place chicken in large, shallow baking dish.
Add onions, garlic, peppers, celery and carrots.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add wine.
Cut butter or margarine into pats and add to mixture.

title: caesar salad double
directions: In a large mixing bowl, squeeze garlic with press.
Discard skins.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar, oil, lemon juice and eggs in that order.
Using whisk, beat until thick.
Add cheese and whisk again.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve package of Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; mix well.
Then add pineapple, pecans and celery.
Pour into Jell-O mold or 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Chill until set. This is good served with either turkey or ham.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt butter; dip chicken in butter, then in mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook down for several hours.
Can in pint jars.
Serve with roast beef or pork.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and eggs together.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine cocoa, butter, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: ziti
directions: Cook macaroni.
Fry mild sausage; drain and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper; add garlic, oregano, salt, pepper and whole tomatoes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add sausage.

title: fruit dip(serves 8)
directions: Beat softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme together until smooth.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine the first 6 items in large bowl, tossing lightly. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Combine vinegar, oil, water and sugar.
Mix well until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Drain and serve in a lettuce lined bowl.
Yields 8 servings.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine ground beef, 1/4 cup soup, egg, 1/4 cup milk, bread crumbs, onion and pepper.
Shape into 6 patties and arrange in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Heat, covered with wax paper, 18 to 19 minutes, giving dish 1/2 turn after 9 minutes.
Drain and let stand, cover 5 minutes.
In small glass bowl, combine remaining soup, mushrooms and milk; heat 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once. Pour sauce over patties and garnish, if desired, with parsley.

title: "easy" green beans
directions: Place beans, 1/4 cup water and bacon bits in saucepan.
Mix soup mix in cup of hot water; add to beans.
Bring to boil. Dissolve cornstarch in 3 tablespoons of cold water; add to beans. Cook about 2 minutes more.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken livers
directions: Rinse livers and drain.
Dip livers in egg and milk mixture, then into flour.
Fry in large skillet for about 5 minutes on each side.

title: linguine a la rocca(burks)
directions: Saute lobster meat real quick.
Add herbs, diced tomatoes and cream.
Do not overcook.
Cook only a few minutes until lobster meat is done.
Add noodles and garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and water in pre-warmed quart Mason jar.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add to milk in a measuring cup; set aside.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix ingredients and chill 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in crock-pot or double boiler.
Use toothpicks to dip balls in chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: asparagus medley
directions: In microwavable dish, cook onion in butter for 2 minutes on High in microwave.
Add potatoes and carrots with water; cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Make/bake 2 (8-inch) unbaked pie shells. Melt oleo. Mix all other ingredients and bake in unbaked pie shells 30 to 40 minutes at 350° on bottom shelf of oven. Makes 2 good size 8-inch pies.

title: lime party salad
directions: Melt in top of double boiler, marshmallows and milk.
Pour hot mixture over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved, then stir in cream cheese with blender.
Remove from blender; add pineapple.
Cool. Fold in whipping cream whipped together with mayonnaise.
Chill until firm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams.
Reserve liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to measure 3 cups.
In large pot, add all ingredients to liquid, except clams.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Mash lightly to thicken. Add clams.
Heat through.
Serves 3.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Warm crust before putting in custard.
Beat eggs slightly (just enough to mix yolks and whites).
Add sugar and salt.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour immediately into crust.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes until crust is brown.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until pie is coagulated to within 1/2-inch of the center.
An inch of liquid in center will continue cooking after pie is removed from oven.

title: homemade muffins
directions: Sift flour, measure, resift three times with the salt, baking powder and sugar, ingredients the last time in a mixing bowl.
Beat egg, add milk and melted butter (pour in the middle of dry ingredients).
Stir until dry ingredients are just dampened, then stir 4 or 5 more times.
Spoon into muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown sausage and garlic.
Add to sauce.
Mix cottage cheese, parsley, beaten eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Layer in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan:
noodles, cheese mix and meat sauce; repeat.
Top each layer with Mozzarella.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream 1/3 sugar with butter and salt.
Blend extract, 2 tablespoons milk and remaining sugar.
Gradually stir in remaining milk.
Will frost layer cake or 24 cupcakes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash and dry romaine lettuce; tear into bite size pieces. Place all other ingredients, except croutons, into blender and process 15 to 20 seconds or until mixed thoroughly.
Place romaine into bowls.
Add croutons, pour dressing over.
Toss thoroughly, add a little extra Parmesan cheese and serve immediately.
Great with garlic bread.

title: dill and sour cream potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover for 15 minutes or until tender; drain and let cool.
Add other ingredients. Chill and garnish with hard-boiled egg slices.

title: turtles
directions: Heat caramels and water on High until melted and smooth.
Stir in walnuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and refrigerate. Dip into chocolate and cool.

title: lucille's fruit punch
directions: Mix together.
Stir until sherbet melts.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 60.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs. Stir in corn.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Fry like corn bread in hot skillet or griddle until brown.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix and spoon onto aluminum foil.

title: beef stew
directions: Season beef with salt, pepper
and sprinkle flour to cover meat.
Saute beef in onions and garlic until brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except potatoes.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.
Add white potatoes.
Cut potatoes in eighths.
Cover and let simmer for 1 hour.

title: kingdom cookies
directions: Follow Numbers 11:8.
Mix thoroughly, cover and chill dough one hour.
Roll out dough and cut into heart shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes. Decorate with sprinkles

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in foil lined pan; salt to taste. Dilute chicken soup with 1/2 can of water.
Pour over chicken and dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Place in 350° oven and bake 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: granny clampett's spring tonic
directions: Mix well and store in an airtight jar.
Use 2 to 3 tablespoons per cup of hot water.
Yields about 28 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese and condensed milk in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding (dry), milk and vanilla. Add to cream cheese mixture. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas, then mixture in a large container or several small containers.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator or for several hours.

title: pop-up bread
directions: Measure 1 1/2 cups of flour into a large bowl and stir in the yeast.
In a saucepan, place the milk, water, oil, sugar and salt. Set over low heat and heat only until warm, stirring to blend.
Add liquid ingredients to flour and yeast mixture; beat until smooth. Blend in eggs.
Add enough additional flour to make a stiff batter; beat until smooth and elastic.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased 1-pound coffee cans.
Cover with plastic, snap on lids and place in a warm spot for dough to rise, about 1 hour.
When dough has almost reached the top of the cans, remove lids and bake in a preheated 375° oven until bread is high and well browned, about 35 minutes.

title: kissing cookies
directions: Let butter soften.
Mix in confectioners sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix.
Mold dough around Kisses.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: topsy turvey apple pecan pie
directions: Spread softened butter evenly on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Press pecan halves, round sides down, in butter.
Pat brown sugar evenly over pecans.
Roll out enough pastry for 1 crust.
Place in pie pan over sugar.
Trim, leaving 1/2 inch overhang.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in walnut-size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook rotini; drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Gradually stir in broth and cream.
Cook over low heat; stir constantly. Blend in cheeses.
Stir constantly until cheese melts.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Continue to heat and stir until heated through.
Easy, quick and very delicious!

title: dump cake
directions: Pour, in order, the listed ingredients into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: kentucky wonder cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients. Beat in egg whites.
Put in hot water, pineapple and nuts.
Pour in tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and boil approximately 10 minutes in slightly salted water. Drain squash. Mix all other ingredients together, using only 1/2 of dressing mix. Place the mixture in a casserole dish or pan. Cover with remaining dressing mix. Cook in oven, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Check top in 30 minutes. If too brown, cover with foil for rest of cooking time.

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add bell pepper, onion, chili powder, tomatoes and rice.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Spread cheese over top; put back in oven until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: boiled white icing
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup; stir well.
Cook to a soft ball stage or 240° on candy thermometer.
Pour syrup over stiffly beaten egg whites; beat until icing hold its shape.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Bake the same as other fruit pies.

title: cheese and beer soup
directions: Saute the kielbasa until golden brown on all sides in a large, hot soup pot, about 4 minutes per side.
The sausage will not be cooked through.
It will finish cooking in the soup.
Remove from the pan and set aside.
In a large pot, heat the oil over medium-high heat.
Add the onions, salt, pepper and bay leaves; cook, stirring until the onions are slightly caramelized, 12 to 15 minutes.
Add the garlic and cook, stirring until fragrant, about 1 minute.
Sprinkle the flour over the onions and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Gradually whisk in the stock and beer. Add the thyme and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.
During the last 15 minutes of cooking, add the kielbasa and cook until sausages are cooked through.
Remove the cooked sausages from the soup.
Add the cheese, 1/3 cup at a time, stirring until nearly all melted and smooth after each addition.
Remove from the heat and adjust the seasoning to taste.
Ladle into 1 or more thermoses. Place sausages in each thermos.
The hot soup will keep the sausage warm until you are ready to eat it.
Pack a roll for the sausage as well.
When it is time to eat the soup, remove the kielbasa and place it on the roll; soup and a sandwich on the go!
Garnish with parsley, garlic croutons and finely grated cheese.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan macaroons
directions: Beat egg white very stiff.
Fold in sugar.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
(I put wax paper and grease it.)
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch chewies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar over low heat.
Stir constantly and bring to a boil.
Cool slightly and add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoonful.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kid-easy s'mores
directions: Place saltines on cookie sheet in a single layer.
Slice cheese thin to fit on top of crackers.
Top cheese with 1/2 marshmallow. Place in oven at 400° until marshmallows brown.
Remove from oven and serve warm.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes according to instant package instructions or cook peeled and quartered baking potatoes in boiling water for 30 minutes until tender. Drain. Mash with potato masher. Add butter and milk. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Set aside. Cook ground beef in a skillet until brown. Drain fat. Add tomato soup and corn (drained, if canned). Mix and transfer to 13 x 9 baking dish. Smooth into bottom layer. Layer mashed potatoes onto beef/soup/corn mixture. Top with cheese. Bake at 300° until heated throughout.

title: blonde peanut brittle
directions: Butter a large cookie sheet; set aside.
Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in heavy 10-inch skillet.
Stir to mix.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat slightly, but keep mixture boiling as rapidly as possible, without boiling over.
Boil about 20 minutes or until syrup turns a very light tan.
Do not overbrown.
Remove from heat.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to 255° (a little dropped into cold cup of water forms a hard ball).

Remove from heat and pour, beating constantly, in a fine stream into the beaten egg whites which have been beaten stiffly in a large mixing bowl. Continue beating until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Add the vanilla.
Drop quickly by tip of spoon onto waxed paper in individual peaks.
I put halves of walnuts on top of some.

title: monkey bread
directions: You will need one nonstick angel food pan.

title: wheat bran bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Add margarine, sugar and salt to hot milk. Stir until margarine is melted, then let cool to room temperature. Stir milk mix into yeast until blended. Stir in bran and enough wheat flour to make soft dough. Place dough on a lightly floured surface and knead in enough remaining flour to make smooth dough. Knead until smooth and elastic. Place in a bowl, sprayed with non-fat cooking spray. Turn dough over once. Cover and let rise 90 minutes (1 1/2 hours). Spray loaf pan. Punch dough down. Shape into 1 loaf and put in pan. Cover and let rise until slightly above pan. Preheat oven to 375°. Brush bread or spray lightly with water; bake 30 to 35 minutes until bread sounds hollow when tapped on top. Cool on wire rack. Makes 1 loaf.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix.
Spread on platter. Top with chopped tomatoes, shredded lettuce and shredded cheese (onions are optional).
Serve with chips.

title: ham-cream cheese appetizers
directions: Spread cream cheese on slice of ham.
Wrap around a tiny pickle.
Roll and slice.

title: elegant steak
directions: Brown meat in oil over high heat.
Put in casserole.
Cover with onions and mushrooms.
Mix soup and liquid from mushrooms. Pour over steak.
Cover casserole and cook 1 hour at 350°. Delicious over rice.

title: pie crust
directions: This recipe makes 5 crusts.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and Crisco together until mixture is crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat together the egg, vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture until well blended.
Using a little flour on your hands, separate the dough into 5 portions.
Chill 1/2 hour before using.
This dough can be frozen in individual, ready-to-use portions.
A tourist in Madeira Beach, Florida gave me this recipe years ago.
My favorite crust!

title: mom's christmas salad
directions: Cream mayonnaise with cream cheese; add mayonnaise, whipped cream, pineapple, cherries, and cut up marshmallows.
Put in freezer trays.
Either freeze and take out just before serving or refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread guacamole dip on bean dip.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top of dips.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: quick chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Prepare rice as directed on the package.
In large skillet, combine chicken, vegetables, bouillon and oil.
Give 4 good shakes of pepper and 4 good shakes of ginger to the skillet; stir until chicken is cooked.
Experiment!
Open bag of rice into skillet; stir and serve.

title: chicken and rice salad
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix chicken, rice, celery and onion. Add French dressing, Miracle Whip and salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate.

title: baked pasta family style
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
In large frying pan, saute oil, beef and garlic until meat is tender; drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except the cheese for topping and the pasta.
Simmer the mixture while cooking the pasta (10 to 13 minutes).
Drain the pasta and mix with the sauce.
Pour into a 3-quart glass rectangular baking dish and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes or until it is bubbly hot.

title: julie's monster cookies
directions: Use extra large bowl.
Mix all ingredients in order.
Drop by large spoonfuls and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls.
Put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork to flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: grady's broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a heavy pot, saute onion until limp.
Add broccoli and parsley and simmer 3 minutes.
While stirring, sprinkle in flour and stir until absorbed.
Transfer to blender and add chicken broth.
Blend until liquified.
Return to pot and add remaining ingredients.
This can be frozen.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again with sugar and salt.
Put butter, water and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry mixture.
Mix eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla and add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Start making frosting the last 5 minutes cake is cooking.

title: good cookies
directions: Beat butter, brown sugar and white sugar together.
Add eggs, vanilla, Hershey bar, chocolate pieces, nuts, oats, flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sinfully low-fat black forest trifle
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions with skim milk and let chill in refrigerator.
Break pound cake into moderate size pieces to cover bottom of trifle dish or large glass bowl. Spread 1/4 of the pudding over cake layer. Top
with layer of cherries and dollop with Cool Whip.
Repeat layers to top of bowl, reserving a few cherries for garnish.
The last layer should be the remainder of the pudding. Decorate with cherries and whipped cream. Chill before serving.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (no salt).
Bone chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Save a few stuffing crumbs and sprinkle them on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Skin and debone chicken breasts.
Cut into finger size pieces. Dip in egg and milk mixture and deep fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind cabbage and onions.
Cover well with hot water.
Let stand 30 minutes and drain.
Grind pepper and mix with cabbage and onions.
Add the seasonings, vinegar and sugar.
Put pickling spice in cloth bag and boil with mixture.
Cool until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Put in jars and seal.

title: spicy apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl cream together butter, brown sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix well and set aside.

title: pastry squares
directions: Combine shortening, 1 cup of sugar and flour.
Mix until crumbly and press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Mix cornstarch and water with applesauce, lemon juice and rind. Simmer slowly for 5 minutes.
Beat eggs, remaining sugar and melted butter.
Stir into cooked cornstarch mixture.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and blend well.
Spread over baked pastry. Then bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Chill before serving.
Makes 18 to 20 squares.

title: tortellini-pesto salad
directions: For pesto, combine parsley, basil and garlic.
Cover and process in a food processor until finely chopped.
Add Parmesan. Process until blended.
Add oil a little at a time; set aside.

title: vanilla cream pie filling or pudding
directions: In saucepan mix flour, sugar and salt; add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium, heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add small amount of cooked mixture to beaten egg yolks, then add this mixture to the cooked mixture.
Return to heat, cooking until it begins to boil.
Remove; add vanilla and butter; cool.

title: grandma jewell's salad dressing cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add salad dressing and water.
Blend well, adding vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sugar-free pineapple dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon raisin oat bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and soda; mix well. Stir in butter until evenly mixed.
Remove 1 cup crumb mixture; set aside.
Pat remaining mixture into greased 9-inch square pan. Combine raisins and jelly; toss with reserved crumb mixture. Sprinkle over layer in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cut while warm.
Cool in pan.
Drizzle with Cinnamon Icing.

title: "nine's" coconut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except pie shells).
Pour mixture into pie shells.

title: aggression cookies*
directions: In a large bowl, mix with your hands the shortening, sugar, oatmeal, flour and baking soda. Add Macadamia nuts and chips (we like white best) and mix in until well blended. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 8 dozen.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Combine egg yolks and milk in a medium saucepan, blending well.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir into egg mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour hot filling into bowl; cover with waxed paper and chill.

title: soy sauce marinade
directions: Mix together over low heat.

title: marco polo beef
directions: Brown meat and onions together in a skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Cover tightly and simmer 45 to 50 minutes. Serve with buttered spaghetti noodles.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: great american potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, eggs and mayonnaise; mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and onion in 1/2 c. water about 15 mintues.
Drain thoroughly.
Add cream cheese and blend.
Add nutmeg to taste, salt and pepper.
Put in small baking dish or individual 3-inch ramkins. Cover with thick layer of sour cream.

title: mexican breakfast one plate
directions: Set oven to 550°.
Heat 1 tortilla in a dry skillet just until hot.
Take out.
Put on plate; set aside.
Fry eggs over-easy; put them on tortillas.
Spread a small amount of salsa over the eggs. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Put plate in oven until cheese is melted, about 1 minute.
Put butter in skillet.
Heat another tortilla and repeat.
Put butter on the second one and serve as bread.

title: pizza popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl.
Melt butter in a small saucepan; add remaining ingredients.
Pour over popcorn and toss until evenly coated.
Place popcorn in a large, ungreased baking pan or cookie sheet.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 12 minutes.
Yield: 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Combine in buttered casserole dish the chicken and 1/2 cup almonds. Mix celery, eggs, Miracle Whip lite, soup, lemon juice, pimento, salt and pepper.
Add this to the chicken and almonds. Then top with chow mein noodles and last 1/2 cup of almonds.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 1 large loaf pan or 2 smaller pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until top starts to brown.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Dissolve sugar in syrup; cook until clear.
Add peanut butter and blend.
Pour over corn flakes.
Drop on wax paper with tablespoon to cool.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: angel frost
directions: In blender, place first four ingredients in order given; blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
(Garnish with fresh fruit if desired.)
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Put foil on cookie sheet.
Roll meat in about 1-inch balls and brown in 350° oven until cooked.
Drain off fat.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: pecan crunch fudge
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and milk in a 3-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat, stir in butterscotch morsels and marshmallow cream.
Beat vigorously with a wooden spoon until mixture is smooth and beginning to cool.
Stir in pecans, brickle and vanilla.
Spread mixture evenly in 2 buttered 8-inch square pans.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Gently press a pecan in top of each square of fudge, if desired.
Store in airtight container.

title: microwave minestrone soup
directions: To serve 6:
Using a 3-quart microwave bowl or casserole dish, cook the bacon pieces on High 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute. Blot with paper napkin to absorb grease.
Stir in onion and garlic and microwave, covered, on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in celery and carrots and 1 tablespoon water, then cover and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in all else except zucchini, then cover and cook on High 10 minutes.
Stir; add zucchini, then cover and cook on High 5 minutes more.
Macaroni and vegetables should be tender.
Stir and let cool 2 to 3 minutes before serving.
Pass the grated Parmesan cheese.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
May be put in blender for a few seconds.

title: baked apples
directions: You will need tinfoil.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread according to directions. Allow to cool. Take out of pan and tear apart in small pieces with hands. Then add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into loaf, but not too thick. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with ketchup.

title: sour cream posy rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Heat sour cream, water and butter until very warm (120° to 130°). Stir in 1 egg and enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead lightly to make soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic, 4 to 6 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 equal pieces. Roll into smooth ball.
Place on greased baking sheet. Fill a shallow pan 1/2 full with boiling water.
Place baking sheet on pan to rise 20 minutes.
Make 6 (3/4-inch) snips around edge.
Beat remaining egg. Brush on rolls. Sprinkle with seed. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender.
Makes 3 small glasses.

title: popover pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, tomato sauce and water. Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into greased pan; top with slices of cheese.
Place in oven to keep warm.
Beat eggs, milk and oil until foamy.
Beat in flour and salt until batter is smooth.
Pour batter over hot meat mixture, spreading to cover.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° or until puffed and brown. Cut and serve immediately.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: In a large skillet, combine all ingredients except the chicken.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes longer. Brush mixture over chicken, then broil chicken, bone side up, on a rack, under the broiler for 8 minutes.
Brush frequently with sauce.
Turn chicken over and continue broiling (and brushing sauce) for another 8 minutes or until chicken is tender.
When done, pour any remaining sauce over chicken.
Serve hot or cold.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Whisk in cream, stirring until thickened.
Add corn; season and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: super chunk jumbles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in white chocolate, walnuts and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 1 1/2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 2 to 3 minutes. Remove to a wire rack to cool.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together good.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Grease cake pan.
Place flour, cocoa, sugar and salt in bottom of pan.
Make 3 holes.
Put oil in one, vinegar in one and vanilla in one.
Pour 1 cup of cold water over ingredients and mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Check after about 20 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crust at 400° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Soften cream cheese and blend in seasonings to taste.
Cover crust with cream cheese spread.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables liberally over crust.
Press vegetables lightly into cream cheese.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown on top.
Serves 6.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix lettuce, beans, tomato, onion and bell pepper.
At last minute, add cheese, chips and dressing.

title: brownies
directions: Combine pudding mix, flour and baking powder; mix well.
Melt butter in saucepan; remove from heat and add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Blend in vanilla and pudding mixture; stir in nuts. Spread in 8 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool in pan, then cut into bars.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and oats.
In another bowl, beat butter, eggs and honey with an electric mixer until blended.
Mix in carrots.
Add flour mixture; stir until mixed, then beat until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon dough in tablespoon-size mounds 2-inches apart on buttered 12 x 15-inch baking sheets; gently flatten dough.
Bake in a 350° oven until cookies feel firm when touched, 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Serve or store airtight up to 2 days. Freeze to store longer.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Blend and chill the first 3 ingredients.
Shape into 2 dozen balls and press into mini muffin pans (on bottom and sides). Blend remaining ingredients.
You need about 2/3 to 1 cup coarsely broken pecans.
Put 1/2 of pecans in pastry-lined pans.
Fill with egg/sugar filling and top with remaining pecans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until set.
Cool and remove from pans.
Delicious!

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef. Add onion and green pepper and cook 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 4 to 6 hours.
If using slow cooker, simmer on low for 12 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain potatoes if canned.
Add sugar, eggs, spices, margarine and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered casserole.

title: stuffed cube steaks
directions: Wipe steaks with a damp cloth; roll in mixture of salt, pepper and flour.
Combine crumbs, poultry seasoning, onion, margarine and water to make a stuffing.
Place steaks with cut side up and cover each with 1/4 of the stuffing.
Fold steaks and fasten with skewers or toothpicks and place in greased shallow baking dish. Place rice around meat rolls.
Add tomatoes, salt and butter. Cover dish and bake in moderate 350° oven for about 1 hour, until tender.

title: cowboy goulash
directions: Brown hamburger
meat; drain fat.
Add flour and let it brown. Add the other ingredients, except beans and cook until well seasoned.
Add
pork
and
beans
and cook about 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.
Great with a salad and garlic bread.

title: hot artichoke cheese dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix and distribute evenly over the bottom of a well-greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Scatter the chiles on top.
Carefully spread mayonnaise over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and chill if made ahead.
Heat at 350°, covered, until hot and bubbly (about 30 minutes).
Serve with Tostitos or crackers.
Delicious! Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a medium bowl, using a whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the Cool Whip.
Spread evenly in the bottom of a crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer, reserving several for garnish, if desired.

title: creole chops
directions: Brown chops after sprinkling with salt, pepper and paprika in very little fat (enough to barely cover bottom of pan).
Leave in skillet and add rice and water over chops.
Place 1 slice each of tomato, onion and green pepper on chops.
Cover and cook on low 45 minutes.

title: mushroom-potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 25 to 30 minutes, or until tender.
Drain and cool to touch.
Peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices; set aside.
Saute mushrooms in butter in a large skillet until tender; set aside.
Combine soup, milk and onion in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Place potatoes in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with mushrooms, reserving 1/2 cup.
Spoon soup mixture over mushrooms.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Garnish with reserved mushrooms.

title: green peas and potatoes in cream
directions: Combine half and half and butter or margarine in saucepan. Place over very low heat and allow butter to melt.
Add potatoes. Cover and allow to simmer slowly until potatoes are almost tender. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer very slowly until peas are tender, about 5 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fajitas
directions: Blend oil, lime juice, fajita seasoning and meat.
Marinate 2 hours.
Drain; reserve marinade.
In heavy frying pan, on high, heat 4 tablespoons marinade.
Add peppers and onion; saute. Remove.
Add 2 tablespoons marinade to frying pan.
Add meat; stir until cooked (3 to 5 minutes).
Remove.
Pour remaining marinade into pan; cook 1 minute.
Pour over meat and peppers.
Add cilantro; toss.
Serve on tortilla covered in cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Remove all skin, wash and dry chicken. Soak chicken in mixture for 2 hours or more.
Cook, uncovered, for about 1 1/2 hours or until glazed at 350°.

title: bertha krivacek watkin's kolachy
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Dissolve sugar in scalded cream and cool to lukewarm.
Add to yeast.
Cut butter into flour as for pie crust.
Add yeast mixture and egg yolks, stirring and beating to form smooth, soft dough.
Cover tightly and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour.

title: no bake cake
directions: Heat butter and milk on top of stove.
Add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Pour mixture over crushed graham crackers.
Stir.
Add coconut and pecans to mixture and stir to blend all ingredients well.
You can use a cake pan to form cake. Then it is ready to eat.

title: spinach onion dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well. Blend all ingredients in a bowl. Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours. Serve with vegetables or cubed rye bread.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients except catsup.
Pack lightly into 9-inch glass dish making a well in center.
Place empty glass right side down in center of dish.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes turning after 3 minutes.
Drizzle catsup over top. Microwave at High for 5 minutes, turning after 2 1/2 minutes. Rest 5 minutes.
Remove glass, baste off drippings.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: easy kolackys
directions: Mix butter, flour and whipping cream until smooth.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut in circles.
Put thump print in middle and fill with fruit filling.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes; then cool and dust with powdered sugar. Makes 5 dozen.

title: elba's pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin. Sift next 8 ingredients together.
Add to pumpkin mixture. Add water.
Pour into loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In a large bowl, beat together sugar, butter, vanilla and milk until smooth.
If necessary, add more milk (a teaspoon at a time), until frosting is spreading consistency. Stir to blend.
Makes enough to frost 2 layer cake or 13 x 9-inch cake or 2 dozen cupcakes.
Makes great filling for graham cracker sandwich cookies.
Can add sprinkles or mini chocolate chips.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mash shrimp fine with a fork and blend with remaining ingredients; form into a ball.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion with meat (drain grease).
Add drained green beans and soup.
Stir together.
Pour into casserole.
Mash potatoes with milk and seasonings.
Spoon onto meat and beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine or shortening, egg, almond extract and vanilla extract together.
Add flour, salt and confectioners sugar.
Divide dough in half and add red food coloring to one of the halves.
With well floured hands roll balls of dough into strips about 4 inches long.
Placing a red and a plain strip together twist and then shape into a cane.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs and egg whites.
Beat until blended and smooth.
Mix in sugar, cinnamon, allspice, ginger and salt, blending well.
Stir in crumbs.

title: french dressing
directions: Grate onion in blender.
Blend remaining ingredients in blender.

title: honey cookies
directions: Gradually beat honey into shortening.
Add eggs; beat well. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan.

title: chili casserole
directions: Cook noodles and set aside. Shred cheese and set aside.
Brown hamburger and drain. Then add chili mix, tomato sauce and beans. Layer with half of chili mixture, cheese and noodles.
Repeat. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon in large bowl; mix well.
Add eggs and oil, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon into 3 well-greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Spread favorite frosting between layers and over top and side of cake.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Grease pan.
Mix and cream margarine and sugar; stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on pan.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: russian corn bread
directions: Mix together. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or longer.

title: patio beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Saute onions in bacon drippings.
Combine all ingredients, except bacon, and place in 3-quart deep dish casserole.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with crumbled bacon and cook 15 minutes.

title: "forget the cookies just give me that batter" chocolate chips
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small pan, melt butter.
While it's hot, add both sugars.
Stir; let cool.
Mix flour, soda and salt in bowl.
In small bowl, beat egg with fork.
Add egg and vanilla to butter mixture and stir.
Add butter, egg and vanilla to flour mixture.
Stir again, then add chips and nuts.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Put rolled, walnut size balls on ungreased cookie pan.
Bake 12 minutes.
Don't overcook.
YUM!

title: seabreeze salad
directions: Dissolve jello and add cold water.
Set until thick.
Stir in pie filling and beat with mixer.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture. Add pineapple to remainder.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch loaf cake pan and let cool until set.
Prepare Dream Whip and fold in remaining 1 cup.
Spread on top and refrigerate.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix sugar and jello as directed on jello package.
Cool. Freeze in large containers.
Thaw slightly.
Add ginger ale to serve.

title: easy chocolate freeze
directions: Line 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with waxed paper strips that extend over sides of pan.
Mix crumbs with 6 tablespoons melted margarine and set aside.
Melt 7 squares chocolate and 1/4 cup margarine over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Beat in sugar at high speed of electric mixer until thick, about 10 minutes.
Fold in chocolate mixture and vanilla, then 4 cups of whipped topping.
Spoon about 1 1/2 cups of chocolate mix into pan.
Sprinkle with 2/3 cup of cookie crumbs.
Press lightly. Repeat layers, ending with crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight until firm.
Melt remaining chocolate.
Cool.
Invert dessert onto plate.
Remove waxed paper.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and drizzle with melted chocolate.
Store in freezer.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt the margarine and let cool. Mix together eggs, corn meal mix, margarine, cottage cheese, onions and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until slightly brown in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: spider cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch in double boiler until runny, about 5 minutes.
Put peanuts and noodles in pan and stir gently, 4 to 5 minutes.
Drop on wax paper using two soup spoons (full).
Cool and serve.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: quick cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; drain.
Cover with the 5% brine.
Let set overnight; drain.

title: homemade biscuit pudding
directions: Soak biscuits in water until soft.
Squeeze water out of biscuits with hand.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Pour in well-greased iron skillet or greased muffin cups.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Pour into buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: homemade mounds candy
directions: Mix coconut, nuts and milk together.
Leave in bowl and place in the freezer for about an hour.
Remove from freezer.
Shape in walnut size balls and dip in the melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper until set.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Then put in slow cooker.
Add regular
Velveeta and Mexican Velveeta. Add salsa to taste.
Heat until warm and cheese is melted.
Dip tortilla chips and enjoy.

title: appetizer tortillas
directions: Mix the Hidden Valley Ranch dressing with the cream cheese and green onions that are sliced.
Set aside.
Then drain the black olives, green chilies and diced pimentos.
Pat them dry on paper towel.
Spread the mixture of the first items set aside on the tortillas and sprinkle the drained ingredients evenly on top. Roll the tortillas tightly and chill 2 hours.
Cut in 1-inch slices.

title: julie's chocolate pies
directions: Heat chocolate chips and margarine until melted.
Mix eggs, pecans, coconut and sugar.
Mix both mixtures together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and cook for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: championship chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar. Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine condensed milk, egg and vanilla.
Spread evenly over prepared crust. Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Add to pretzels. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Cool completely.

title: cathedral window candy
directions: Melt in double boiler the eggs, butter and chocolate chips. Let cool.
Mix well with the marshmallows and pecans.
Powder 3 sheets wax paper with powdered sugar.
Divide mixture into thirds and roll each portion to about 1 1/2 x 10-inches.
Wrap well. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch while cold.

title: a luscious lemon cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large chilled mixing bowl.
Beat until very thick.
Garnish with fresh fruit.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: dipped candies
directions: Melt bark in microwave and dip crackers, cookies and pretzels. Lay on waxed paper or cookie racks to harden.

title: wyoming-mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in dry taco mix, salt, water and taco sauce.
Add chopped frozen spinach (can be defrosted quickly in microwave if in a hurry).
Add ham, cover, cook until thoroughly heated.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In another skillet, heat oil. Dip tortillas, one at a time, into oil until soft and limp, 5 to 10 seconds only.
Drain on paper towels.
Add 1/3 cup of meat mixture to each shell, roll up.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Spread sour cream then cheese on top, return to oven to melt cheese (5 to 10 minutes).

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased baking pan or dish.
Frozen peas may be added if desired.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: 3-day old coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, coconut and sour cream and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake cake as directed on box and cool, then slice layers in two.
Spread mixture between layers except for one cup. Add that one cup to the Cool Whip and use to frost top and sides of cake.
Put on cake plate in refrigerator and let set for 3 days before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat.
Drain grease.
Add soup and simmer.
Add ketchup and seasoning as desired.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: green pistachio jello salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple and juice; mix well. Then add Cool Whip and mix well. Add all the marshmallows and again mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: butterscotch clusters
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter in microwave (careful not to burn peanut butter).
Stir to mix.
Add peanuts and stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool and serve.
Can store in fridge.

title: crunchies(breakfast)
directions: Melt margarine over a pot of boiling water. Add Golden Syrup and baking soda. Add oats, sugar, flour and coconut. Smooth into pan. Bake at 325° for 5 to 7 minutes. Turn off oven and leave in for an additional 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
In saucepan, bring to a boil, butter, water and cocoa.
Add this to flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well. Add eggs, buttermilk, soda, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Cook in greased 11 x 16-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamy tuna dip
directions: Drain tuna; flake.
Combine tuna, onion salt, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish and sour cream.
Cover; chill.
Garnish with parsley and surround with potato chips.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix as for plain yellow cake.
Bake about 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pumpkin bake
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).

title: potato salad
directions: This recipe serves 200 to 250.

title: lillie's apple squares(low-fat)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add apples and stir to blend.
Set aside.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to apple mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased or sprayed 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: karo caramels
directions: Melt butter, sugar and syrup.
Add 1 cup milk and cream of tartar.
Cook fast, stirring and adding remaining milk, 1 cup at a time, about every 5 minutes.
Cook slow until crack stage (248°). Fold in nuts.
Pour in greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Cut with scissors.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Twist ends.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
Debone and cut chicken in bite-size pieces. Dip tortillas in chicken stock until wilted.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Dissolve lime in 2 gallons of water and add cucumbers, which have been scrubbed and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Soak for 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Make a picking solution of vinegar, sugar, salt, cloves, allspice and celery seed (tie the last 3 up in a cloth).
Soak cucumbers in this solution for 3 hours, then boil for 30 minutes.
Put into hot jars and seal.
Makes 12 to 14 pints.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients and make into patties.
Fry in skillet until browned.

title: quail and mushroom gravy
directions: Soak quail in buttermilk for at least 30 minutes.
Coat with flour; sprinkle with salt.
Brown in deep fat.
Remove oil but leave pan drippings.
Add 1 can mushroom soup, 1 can water.
Stir together with pan drippings and simmer quail in gravy at least 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening, salt, vanilla and eggs together; gradually add flour, mixed with baking powder.
Mix the buttermilk with baking soda and add, parts at a time.
Drop onto cookie sheet and top with raisins or anything you like.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Make sauce of butter, flour and salt, adding milk gradually along with water.
Cook until thick.
Pour over stiffly beaten egg yolks.
Add salmon.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into sauce. Pour into buttered dish, set into pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture. Spread in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: frosted lemonade punch
directions: In punch bowl, stir cold water into lemonade mix until dissolved.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Stir half the sherbet to soften.
Blend into the lemonade mixture.
Scoop remaining sherbet on top, resting bottle on rim of bowl, carefully pouring 7-Up. Stir gently.
Makes 14 cups.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Combine rice, soups and wine in a covered container and refrigerate overnight. Pour rice mixture in an oblong 9 x 12 x 13-inch glass baking dish that has been buttered.
Place chicken pieces on top and cover with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Remove foil and brown for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, saute onions in butter until transparent but not browned.
Add the sweet potatoes and broccoli.
Saute lightly.
Stir in broth, potatoes and seasonings.
Cook until almost done; add cream and heat through.

title: cinnamon corn
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, syrup, salt and red hots. Cook 5 minutes or until red hots dissolve.
Add soda and stir well.
Pour over popped corn. Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread out and cool.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Put into 2 greased and floured loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: rabbit sauce piquante
directions: Cut rabbits into serving size pieces.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Brown rabbits in shortening, add flour and brown well.
Add onions, celery and garlic.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add water and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour mixture over rabbits.
Cook for 25 minutes or until tender.
Add fresh mushrooms.
Simmer 5 more minutes. Serve with steamed rice.

title: roasted potatoes with rosemary
directions: Cook potatoes in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Cut potatoes in half. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.)

title: cucumber soup
directions: Put cucumber, soup, milk, sour cream and seasonings in blender.
Blend 1 minute.
Chill several hours or overnight.
To serve, stir and pour into small bowls or cups.
Garnish.

title: date log candy
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook until mixture forms a ball in cold water.
Remove from stove.
Add coconut and nuts.
Beat until stiff.
Roll in damp cloth.
Allow to harden and slice in 1/4-inch rounds.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados or puree in blender. Add other ingredients abd mix well. Chill.

title: mixed vegetable dish
directions: Cook vegetables until tender and drain.
Mash eggs with fork and
add
room temperature mayonnaise.
Spread this over the vegetables.
Top with bacon bits.

title: beef ragout
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch cubes.
Dredge in seasoned flour.
Preheat skillet at 6.
Melt shortening and saute garlic.
Add tomato juice, bay leaves, cloves, marjoram, sugar, salt, pepper, parsley and water.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add more water, if needed.
Add whole onions and carrot strips.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Add peas; cover and cook until all vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: peanut butter-honey brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 8 or 9-inch pan. In small bowl, combine peanut butter and honey; blend until smooth. Set aside. In large bowl, combine brownie mix, 1/4 cup butter, water and egg; beat 50 strokes with spoon. Spread half batter in pan. Score batter into 16 squares. Using 1/4 cup of peanut butter mixture, place 1 measuring teaspoon of mixture into center of each square. Carefully spread remaining batter over top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until edges pull away from pan. Cool 45 minutes. Spread remaining peanut butter mixture over brownies. In small saucepan, combine chocolate chips and 3 tablespoons butter; cook over low heat until melted and smooth, stirring constantly. Spread over top of brownies. Cool 45 minutes or refrigerate until set. Cut into bars.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch morsels in 2-quart casserole.
Heat in Radarange oven on Cookmatic level 6 for 5 to 6 minutes, or until melted.
Stir once during melting.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm. Store in airtight container.
Yields 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave.
Mix all ingredients well. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Stir.
Microwave 2 minutes on Medium (50%).
Add soda; stir until foamy.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir well.
Microwave 3 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Spread out to cool.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half.
Remove seeds, wash, cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, tomato sauce and rice.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Fill peppers with mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Put in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In bowl, layer half the lettuce, half the peas and onion.
Add remaining lettuce, peas and the boiled egg (sliced or grated). Blend mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over salad.
Top with cheese.
Best when refrigerated, but loses crispness after several hours.

title: nancy sherman's cranberry-jello salad or dessert
directions: *I like one package dark cherry and one package cherry or strawberry.

title: caraway pork
directions: Place pork cutlets evenly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle heavily with garlic salt and caraway seed.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes to brown.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Combine beans, celery and pimiento.
Dissolve salt and sugar in vinegar and add salad oil.
Cover and shake.
Pour over bean mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Stir occasionally.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine as listed. Mix well. Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate (or two 8-inch foil pans). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Stir until blended, then separate dough into 4 balls.
Roll each ball into 12 (1-inch) balls.
Press each into tiny muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 4 dozen.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Wash garbanzos.
Soak overnight with a tablespoon of salt in sufficient water to cover beans.
When ready to cook, drain the salted water from the beans.
Place in 4-quart soup kettle and add 2 quarts of water, ham and beef bone.
Cook for 45 minutes over slow fire, skimming foam that forms at the top.
Cut salt pork in thin strips and fry slowly in a skillet.
Add chopped onion; saute lightly.
Add to the beans along with potatoes, paprika and saffron.
Add salt to taste.
When potatoes are done, remove from fire.
Add chorizo that has been cut in thin, round slices.
Serves 4.

title: cran-raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve 2 gelatins in boiling water.
Stir in frozen raspberries, breaking up in large pieces.
Break up cranberry sauce with fork; stir into gelatin mixture.
Chill until partially set.
Carefully pour in lemon-lime beverage, stirring gently. Turn into a 6 cup
mold.
Chill 5 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: angel food cake with lemon filling
directions: Bake cake and let cool completely.
Cut to make 3 layers.
Ice between layers with Eagle Brand milk mixed with lemonade (thawed) and small carton Cool Whip.
Ice outside of cake with small carton of Cool Whip.

title: stuffed pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Rub meat with lemon juice. Tear bread slices into crumbs.
Add apples.
Combine corn syrup and peanuts with bread crumbs and apples. Stuff pork and tie securely.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan and roast 50 minutes or until done.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix together flour, salt, egg, milk and salad oil until dry ingredients are moistened. Cut onions into slices 1/4-inch thick. Separate into rings. Coat onions with mixture. Fry in hot oil at 375°.

title: great party rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in an open dish.
I used a 2 x 7 x 10-inch.
Stir 3 or 4 times while cooking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit tart
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in flour and vanilla.
Spread on greased jelly roll pan.
Score into squares and spoon 1 teaspoon fruit pie filling into each square. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: apple jack cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat in egg.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in apples.
Drop in the shape of balls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: budget tuna bake
directions: Cook potatoes in slightly salted water for 10 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour, catsup, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually while stirring.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Arrange potatoes, tuna and onion in Pyrex dish.
Pour sauce over and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf ring
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Add 1/4 cup tomato sauce to meat mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Spoon into 4 or 5-cup ring mold.
Use Cook cycle and cook 20 to 22 minutes.
It is done when meat pulls away from sides of dish.
Let stand 5 minutes, drain.
Invert onto warm serving platter.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix together and roll in chopped pecans.
Serve on graham crackers.

title: chicken casserole #2
directions: Combine margarine and crackers and set aside. Mix chicken, sour cream and chicken soup. Pour 1/2 cracker crumbs mixture in bottom of casserole, then pour chicken over crumbs. Then put remaining crumbs on top. Bake at 350° until brown, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese; cream with butter.
Mix in flour by hand with pinch of ground red pepper.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cheesy wieners
directions: Place on microwavable plate.
Cook on High for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss ingredients just before serving.
Serve with Creamy Italian or Ranch dressing.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom with nuts and coconut. Mix cake according to package directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and melted butter and pour over unbaked cake.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350° or until cake tests done when toothpick is inserted.

title: chicken st. jaques
directions: In saucepan, combine seasoned salt, thyme, green onions, flour, sour cream, parsley and pineapple juice.
Brown chicken in pan with butter.
Cook ingredients together.
When heated, add cheese.
Cook chicken for 1/2 hour, then put sauce on chicken and bake uncovered for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: vera whitley's coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time; blend well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk, alternating, adding flour and buttermilk until all is used, beating well after each addition.
Bake at 325° in four 9-inch pans for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: holiday fudge cut outs
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and salt. Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add semi-sweet morsels.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Spread evenly in aluminum foil lined pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Chill in refrigerator until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Lift out of the pan and peel off the foil.
Allow fudge to soften several minutes.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Decorate with pastry tube, using white or colored frosting.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Combine wafers and butter.
Press into 10-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Soften ice cream and mix in creme de menthe until color is uniform.
Fill wafer shell.
Freeze.

title: squash casserole with sour cream
directions: Mix squash, onion, one teaspoon butter or margarine and soup well.
Mix corn bread stuffing and one stick melted butter or margarine.
Add 3/4 of this mixture to the squash mixture; put in 2-quart dish and sprinkle remaining on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add cheeses until melted.
Add frozen broccoli and mushroom soup.
When heated completely, add can of mushrooms and your almonds.
Serve.

title: 30 day cake
directions: In a gallon container, mix together peaches with juice and 2 1/2 cups of the sugar.
Do not refrigerate.
Stir once a day for 10 days.
On the 10th day, add the pineapple and juice and the other 2 1/2 cups of the sugar.
Stir once a day for 10 days.
On the 20th day, add the fruit cocktail and juice and the maraschino cherries (do not add the juice of the cherries).
Stir once a day for 10 days.
On the 30th day, drain juice from fruit mixture.
Mix together 1 cup of the fruit mixture, cake mix, eggs, vegetable oil, nuts, raisins and coconut until well blended.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes (until done).

title: potato salad
directions: Boil new potatoes whole (with skin on).
Fry bacon crisp and save grease.
Drain bacon.
Crumble when cool.
Saute chopped green onions (tops also) and chopped celery in bacon grease.

title: obel kage(apple cake - danish)
directions: Melt butter in heavy frying pan.
Add crumbs and sugar.
Stir continually until bread crumbs are browned.
Place prepared crumbs in greased loaf pan alternately with layers of applesauce.
Bake in slow oven for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Allow to harden in refrigerator.
Serve cold with whipped cream.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and warm applesauce.
Add spices, eggs, raisins and nuts. Mix flour and soda and add to batter. Mix thoroughly. Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
To store keep tightly wrapped in foil.
Gets better with age if it lasts that long!

title: drew's delights
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass pan with Pam. Mix and press in bottom of pan the cake mix, 1 stick margarine and 1 egg.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over mixture.
Mix sugar, 1 stick margarine, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Spread over top of pecans.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: As I walked down life's lonesome highway a long time ago, I saw a sign that read:
"Heaven's Grocery Store".
As I got a little closer, the door swung open wide...and I stepped inside!
I saw a host of angels, they were standing everywhere...One handed me a basket and said, "My child, go and shop with care.
Everything a Christian needs is in this store; the things you can't carry today...Tomorrow, you can come back for!"

title: minted baby carrots
directions: In large saucepan, combine carrots and salt with water to cover.
Bring to a boil over high heat and cook 20 minutes or until fork-tender; drain.
Return carrots to pan and add butter or margarine and sugar.
Shake pan over low heat to melt butter and glaze carrots.
Sprinkle with mint.

title: hour rolls
directions: Mix together yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and water. Set aside. Combine milk, margarine, 3 tablespoons sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm. Add to yeast mixture.
Add flour and form into soft ball.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Knead 20 times on a floured board. Form into rolls for 9 x 13-inch pan or muffin pan.
Let rise 15 minutes. Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grind nuts, onion, parsley and toast.
Add cheese, well beaten eggs and seasonings; mix well.
Fry in deep fat.
Place in large casserole.
Cover with tomato juice, V-8 or spaghetti sauce.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's green salad
directions: Heat juice and water.
While hot, stir in jello.
Cool and add cream cheese.
When cold, add cream, beaten stiff.
Add crushed pineapple.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy bars in microwave.
Slowly beat melted candy bars into Cool Whip in a large mixing bowl.
Once completely mixed, pour into pie crust.
Top with desired amount of Cool Whip for garnish.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Serve.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter both apples.
(You will have eight quarters.) The crescent rolls have eight sections.
Roll each one out on a floured board as much as possible.
Take one quarter of apple and slice onto one section of crescent rolls.
Bring sides up and pinch together.
Place dumplings in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together sugar, melted margarine and orange juice.
Pour over dumplings. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.
Delicious!
Yield:
Eight dumplings.

title: mom's roast beef
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven; brown roast on all sides.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add coffee, 3/4 cup of water, bouillon, basil, rosemary, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix sauce ingredients together while broccoli is cooking.
Add cooked and drained broccoli and place in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creole okra
directions: Combine all the ingredients and cook until tender.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Reduce to 325° for another 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: Combine in large bowl 1 cup flour, oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and melted butter or oleo.
Press 1/2 of crumbs into bottom of 9-inch square pan that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a heavy pan over medium heat until warm. Add the garlic	and cook until soft. Cut tomatoes into 1-inch pieces and add to the pan along with the basil and optional fennel seed. Cook for 25 minutes, stirring often. Pour into a blender or use a stick blender and puree. Return the sauce to the heat and season with salt and pepper. Simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes to reduce slightly. This sauce is great over fish, pork, poultry or pasta.

title: lulu paste
directions: Heat eggs, sugar and vinegar over low heat until jelled.
Mix with cream cheese (softened), onion and pepper.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetable sticks.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water until tender.
Remove bones and chop meat; set aside.
Cook rice according to package directions. Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, soup, milk and mushrooms.
Layer chicken, rice and sauce in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; top with cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.
Yields 8 servings.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Beat egg whites and gradually add sugar.
Beat well; add nuts and vanilla.
Melt butter in pan and add nut mixture.
Spread in one layer on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Combine caramel ice cream topping and 3 tablespoons of flour and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients (except chocolate pieces and pecans) in a large bowl.
Press half of combined crumb mixture into bottom of 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces and pecans.
Spread carefully with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours. Cut into bars.

title: meat loaf
directions: Cut tomato, onion and pepper.
Mix with meat.
Add egg and cracker crumbs.
Bake in square pan at 325° for 45 minutes.
When meat loaf has cooked 25 minutes, pour 1 small can tomato sauce over it.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Mix all together and let stand for a while for flavors to mix. Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: rip's dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Dice dried beef, green pepper and onion.
Add to cream cheese and sour cream and mix. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Grind vegetables; set aside.
Put other ingredients in large pot. Boil 5 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Boil 5 minutes more. Pour into hot pint jars.
Add lids and process 10 minutes in your canner.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in bottle and shake until well blended.

title: cheddar-pecan cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Then mix together all the ingredients, except for pecans.
Shape into a ball and coat with chopped pecans.

title: breakfast before
directions: Fry sausage until crumbled.
Drain and pour into casserole dish.
Mix eggs, salt, mustard and milk.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
For best flavor, let set overnight in refrigerator.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Freezes well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana flip cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together until well beaten.
Bake in a sheet cake pan at 350° until cake is done, about 30 to 35 minutes. Let cool.

title: "crab ball"
directions: Mix together crabmeat and cream cheese.
Shape into ball. Before serving, top with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: mexican zucchini
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
Add zucchini, carrots, onion, green pepper, garlic, celery, salt, basil and pepper.
Toss to mix well.
Cook, covered, over medium-high heat for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine taco sauce and mustard.
Stir into vegetables.
Add tomato wedges.
Cook, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: red neck caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with corn chips or nacho chips.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Place rice, onion and butter in skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until brown.
Add bouillon and mushrooms.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove cover; bake for 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue kielbasi
directions: Poke kielbasi and microwave to drain grease, 1 to 2 minutes. Mix sauces, then put in crock-pot with kielbasi and other ingredients.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: french onion soup
directions: Thinly chop the onions; saute in butter until limp.
Add flour, garlic and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until golden brown.
In a large pot, put beef broth, chicken broth and white wine.
Add onion mixture; simmer for 45 minutes (pinch of parsley and thyme are optional).
Cut French bread about 1-inch thick and toast.
Place 2 slices of cheese in bottom of soup bowl.
Pour in hot soup; add slice of bread.
Top with another slice of cheese. Place under the broiler until cheese melts.

title: beanhole bash beans
