directions: Have ready 4 very large black iron kettles with tight fitting lids and one fire pit large enough to hold the kettles.

title: tart scalloped cabbage
directions: Parboil cabbage in 1/4 cup salted boiling water; do not drain. Combine eggs, 1/4 teaspoon salt, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Add cabbage and any liquid.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle potato chips over top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: tangy tortilla casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Blend in tomatoes, enchilada sauce, olives, salt and garlic powder.
Beat egg into cottage cheese. Spread 1/3 meat sauce into greased 3 quart casserole or a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of Jack cheese and 1/2 cottage cheese.
Top with 1/2 tortilla halves.
Repeat layers. Cover with remaining meat sauce and top with Cheddar cheese. Border with crushed tortilla chips.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into wedges or squares, depending on the dish it was baked in.
Yields 6 to 8 generous servings.

title: county fair pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the margarine, sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: corn flakes and peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar and Karo and let come to a bubbly boil.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add corn flakes.
Mix and drop onto waxed paper.

title: hashbrown casserole
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Put in casserole dish. Saute cornflakes in butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the cream cheese, margarine and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Divide into 3 parts.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Add to boiling water until you reach your desired taste.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Combine oleo, brown sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Do not stir.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Spread in large baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Break into pieces when cooled. Store in airtight container.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and oleo until mixture is crumbly.
Pack half of the mixture in bottom of cake pan.
Add cranberry sauce.
Place rest of oatmeal mixture on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cool. Cut into squares.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: dilly ham balls
directions: In a bowl, combine ham, bread crumbs, onions, 1 tablespoon fresh dill or 1 teaspoon dried, milk, egg, mustard and half of pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon oil.
Brown ham balls, adding remaining butter and oil as needed.
Remove ham balls to a serving dish.
Cover and keep warm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Alternate milk and flour, ending with flour.
Put soda in with last half of milk.
Add flavorings.
Fold in egg whites.

title: puppy chow(aka muddy buddies)
directions: Pour Chex cereal in large bowl; set aside. Melt chips, peanut butter and margarine in medium saucepan over low heat stirring constantly. Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal and gently stir until all is coated well.

title: peanut butter cookies from cake mix
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter. Add cake mix; blend well. Add beaten eggs, brown sugar and vanilla. Stir in peanut butter chips. Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet; press with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 4 dozen or more cookies.

title: corn flake bars
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter over low heat.
Pour over corn flakes; mix well and flatten in a buttered pan.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Cook, stirring frequently to 232° or until mixture forms very soft ball.
Add caramels and beat until melted and spreading consistency.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute rice in 2 tablespoons oil in skillet until lightly brown. Push to side of skillet.
Saute chopped vegetables in 1 tablespoon of oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and 1/2 cup hot water.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes or until rice is tender, adding small amount of additional hot water if necessary. Let stand uncovered for several minutes before serving.
Garnish with green pepper rings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, mix eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini. Mix well.
Stir together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to sugar mixture, mixing well.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes or until done, depending on oven.

title: orange pineapple fluff cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in Bundt pan (well greased).
Cook about 40 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: cheese cake(torte)
directions: Cream well to soften the cream cheese.
Beat until stiff egg whites and blend in sugar.
Combine with cheese and add vanilla. Pour into 8-inch spring-form pan 3-inches deep, buttered and dusted with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tuna-macaroni shell salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: frosted cranberry squares
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling.
Dissolve jello in this; cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partially set.
Blend pineapple and cranberry sauce and fold in.
Turn into 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Chill until firm.
Prepare dessert topping according to directions.
Fold in cream cheese.
Spread over jello.
Put pecans in 1 tablespoon butter in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Sprinkle over top of jello.
Makes 9 servings.

title: sausage and apples
directions: Cook the sausages in a large saute pan until done, remove and keep warm.
Add the butter to the pan and saute the onions and the apples until the onions are translucent.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Cook until soft.
Drain.
In baking dish, layer potatoes, marshmallows, sugar and nuts.
Put marshmallows, nuts and sugar on top and sprinkle tablespoon of cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Drop spoonfuls of batter into oil in hot frying pan.
Brown both sides.

title: corn fritters
directions: Chop corn and drain.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Sift the flour with salt, baking powder and paprika.
Stir into corn mixture.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg white.
Dip batter by teaspoon and slide it into the heated oil (375°).
Fry until medium brown, 3 or 4 minutes.
Drain.
Serve immediately.

title: sour cream gems
directions: Mix butter and flour together with a fork.
Add sour cream and stir until moistened.
Spoon into greased miniature muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen gems.

title: pasta e fagioli(microwave)
directions: Cook macaroni al dente.
Combine oil and garlic in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook at High for 35 seconds.
Add tomatoes with liquid, basil and pepper.
Cover with wax paper; cook on High for 5 to 8 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in beans and liquid; cover and cook at Medium (50%) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add macaroni. Serve in bowls topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: tomatoes en casserole
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in butter until tender (about 5 minutes).
Add all of the remaining ingredients. Mix.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.**
Bake in 375° oven 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.
This is good hot or cold.

title: orange rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, mix orange juice with water, saffron, Angostura bitters and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Slowly stir in rice.
Stir to blend well.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
Fluff with fork and serve.

title: antipasto
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.

title: easy sweet and sour barbecue sauce
directions: Puree cranberry sauce in the blender or in a food processor. Combine the cranberry puree with the remaining ingredients and heat until brown sugar dissolves.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Place all dry ingredients into large bowl and set aside. Combine oil, eggs and milk.
Beat together and add to dry ingredients.
Fold in rhubarb.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into an oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle a box of cake mix on top of the pie filling.
Pour the melted margarine on and top with the nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring shortening and water to a boil in saucepan; sift flour and salt together.
Add to boiling water all at once, beating vigorously until mixture is thick and smooth so it will not stick to sides of pan.
Remove from burner.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition until smooth.
Drop mixture from teaspoon about 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Mixture should hold its shape and not spread.
Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 8 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400°; bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Should be firm and crisp, but not too brown.
Cool.
Split and fill with pimento cheese, chicken salad, jam or pudding.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Boil, rinse and drain spaghetti, then put into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss with Parmesan cheese and butter.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with pepperoni slices.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut into bite size.
Add celery, chicken, soup and pimento. Add eggs, almonds and chicken broth. Mix all ingredients in baking dish. Crush potato chips over top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in 4 quart casserole.
Add onions, pepper and garlic.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes on High.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add water, stirring to keep smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Microwave 15 minutes on High.
Reduce setting and microwave 50 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: colored popcorn balls(kid recipe)
directions: Place popped corn into a large buttered bowl.
In bottom part of double boiler, heat about 1 inch of water to boiling.
Put top pot in and add marshmallows, butter and salt.
Stir until marshmallows are melted and mixed well.
Add few drops of food coloring.
Pour marshmallow mixture over popcorn and stir gently to coat.
Grease hands well with butter and quickly shape into 10 medium sized balls.

title: afternoon chocolate
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat.
Cool. Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup milk, stirring well. Add cornstarch mixture and remaining milk to reserved chocolate mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Pour into cups and serve immediately with a dollop of whipped cream.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: all in one
directions: Arrange in layers in order given in oblong pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine egg yolks and 1/2 cup of sugar in saucepan; stir in salt and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat and add softened gelatin.
Chill until mixture is about as thick as fresh egg whites.
Fold in sliced berries.
Beat egg whites until they stand in soft peaks.
Gradually beat in 1/4 cup of sugar.
Fold egg whites into the gelatin mixture.
Turn into cooled, baked pie crust.
Chill until ready to serve.
Spread with whipped topping and garnish with whole berries.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: green bean deluxe
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp and drain off all but 2 tablespoons grease.
Crumble bacon.
Put crumbled bacon and chopped onion with butter back in skillet with grease and saute. Add drained green beans and fry until done.
Season with above ingredients to taste.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a food processor, grind cranberries, pecans, oranges with peel and apples with peel. Remove each to large bowl after processing.
Add 1 cup sugar and the pineapple; mix.

title: nut loaves or muffins
directions: Mix all together well. Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours if using two 9 x 5 loaf pans or 55 minutes if using 8 mini loaf pans or 20 to 25 minutes if using mini muffin pan (makes 48).

title: heavenly casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter or oil.
Mix ingredients well and place in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli flowerets 15 minutes.
In large saucepan, melt butter and saute onion until transparent.
Blend in flour and salt, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes.
Gradually add broth, then broccoli, stirring frequently.
Transfer to blender in batches and puree.
Return to saucepan; add milk.
Heat thoroughly until hot.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sirloin and noodles
directions: Brown sirloin in oil. Add onion and cook until tender, then add soy sauce, mushrooms, beef bouillon and 2 cups of the water. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Combine cornstarch and the remaining 1/2 cup water.
Add to mixture. Serve over hot egg noodles.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add well-beaten eggs.
Measure and sift dry ingredients to first mixture.
Add vanilla, chopped apples, pecans and raisins.
Flour and grease pan.
Cook 55 minutes at 350°.
I use tube pan.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice olives; place in bottom of pan.
Beat eggs; mix with cheese.
Pour over olives.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
This is great cold as well as warm.

title: swedish coffee bread
directions: Melt butter, shortening and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoon warm water, add to other ingredients, add flour to knead.
Let rise to double.
Braid into 2 large or 3 small loaves. Brush with egg.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon or frost later.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease
and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread coconut and pecans in
bottom
of pan.
Prepare German chocolate cake mix according to package.
Pour batter over coconut and nuts.
Mix oleo,
cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Pour mixture on top
of
batter (just glob it on by the teaspoonful).
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Cake will be shaky but will set up.
It looks like it has been in an earthquake, thus the name, but do not cook longer than the recipe calls for.

title: salmon kabobs
directions: Cut salmon into 7-inch cubes.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cubed salmon and marinate for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from sauce and place on skewers.
Place skewers across a baking dish. Bake in a moderate oven at 375° for 20 minutes.
Baste once during baking with extra sauce.
Serve on buttered rice.
Serves 6.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: In microwave bowl, mix together brown sugar, salt, sorghum and margarine.
Microwave for three minutes.
Stir.
Microwave again for three minutes.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and mix together.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly to make a white sauce.
Add salt and bouillon to mixture; let cool.
Add well beaten eggs, mayonnaise, chicken and almonds; mix well.
At the last minute, add the chow mein noodles and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until firm and lightly browned.

title: fay's peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar, peanut butter and milk until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: goblin bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs.
Add flour (usually one cup at a time).
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease two 5 x 10-inch pans.
Spread in pans (will be thin).
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese and seasonings.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread with mayonnaise mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° or until cooked through.
Serves 6.

title: grandma aries' cranberry bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Add orange juice, orange rind, sifted flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Add cranberries and chopped nuts and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: sour cream and coconut cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Bake in two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans as directed on cake mix box.
Cool as directed.
When cool, split layers and ice.
Do not ice sides.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pat's cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix spice; add applesauce a little at a time.
Roll out in cinnamon.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Dry for a day.
Nice for closets, bathroom, etc.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Combine in skillet, onion, bell pepper, garlic, ground beef, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until ground beef is done and then drain.
Heat enchilada sauce in pan.
Dip each tortilla in enchilada sauce.
Put a layer of dipped tortillas, ground beef mix, cheese and small amount of enchilada sauce, another layer of dipped tortillas, ground beef mix, cheese and small amount of sauce.
Finally 3rd layer of dipped tortillas and remainder of sauce.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: cookie cutter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg, vanilla, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Then flour and salt until well blended.
Divide dough between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Wrap and flatten into 3/4-inch thick rounds.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
Heat oven to 325°.
On a floured surface, roll dough between 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets until lightly colored, about 12 minutes.
Cool and decorate.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: corn machu with pork
directions: Stir in corn, a little wine, salt, 1 teaspoon hot sauce, soy sauce and lean meat.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Lower flame and cook 1 hour.

title: make ahead brownie mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening until evenly distributed. Store in large, airtight container in pantry.
Keeps 10 to 12 weeks. Yields about 17 cups of mix.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Chill. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: toasted vienna chunks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip bread into condensed milk; allow to drain briefly and roll ini coconut.
Place on greased baking sheet; bake 8 minutes or until coconut is toasted.
Immediately remove from baking sheets.
Store loosely covered at room temperature. Makes 50 to 60 chunks.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Put vinegar, salt and water in large kettle ready for heating. Look over dill and wash.
Pack jars with freshly washed cucumbers, putting a stalk or flower of dill in bottom.
Save a little space for top to place another piece of dill.
Put garlic in each jar and place 1/8 teaspoon alum in each jar.
Heat vinegar solution to just a boil.
Put in jars.
Cover cucumbers.
Seal immediately and store in cool dark place.
Makes 8 to 10 quarts of pickles.
Can be ready to use in 4 to 6 weeks.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Cook 3 large chicken breasts until tender.
In a bowl mix: shredded cheese (half cheddar and half jack), 1-pint whipping cream (not whipped); set aside.
Saute:
onions & garlic; place sauteed vegetables in a large bowl.
Add:
Chicken, olives, La Victoria Thick & Chunky Salsa, and 1 1/2 Cups shredded Jack cheese place small amount of chicken mixture in flour tortilla.
Roll up and place on baking dish.
Pour cream & cheese mixture over top, covering all tortillas.
Let sit for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese melts and enchiladas are thoroughly heated.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large pan, brown onion, green pepper and bacon.
Add creamed corn, water, potatoes and carrots.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
When ready to serve, add milk, butter, salt and pepper to taste.

title: swiss vegie medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can onion rings. Pour into 1-quart casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to boil and boil for five minutes.
Pour solution boiling hot over cukes and seal.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into small cubes.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper. Brown in hot butter.
Add 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup vinegar; simmer until tender.
Add water as necessary to keep from burning. When tender, pour off excess liquid.
Add sour cream, bay leaf, salt, pepper, mushrooms, butter, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover; simmer until everything is heated thoroughly. Don't boil.
Serve over noodles.

title: french green bean casserole
directions: Add milk slowly to mushroom soup, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling point.
Combine green beans and 1/2 can onions in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Pour soup over beans. Sprinkle with cheese and remaining 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine syrup and milk.
Blend well.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts or 18 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop stems and cook in frying pan with oil and garlic.
Add parsley, oregano, salt, pepper, grated cheese and tomato sauce for color.
Mix well and cook for few minutes.
If mixture is dry, add water or chicken broth.
Add seasoned bread crumbs and stuff caps.
Put a little oil on each mushroom before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: collette's water chestnuts
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnuts; secure with wooden toothpicks.
Place on a rack in 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Use fork to slide toothpicks off the water chestnuts (bacon is cooked, so it will remain in place).
Place in 11 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix ketchup and sugar together and pour on top.
Bake an additional hour at 325°.
Use decorative picks to serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Put drained pineapple in greased cake pan.
Add cherry pie filling on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over the pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Pour melted butter over that.
Put pecans on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: In a saucepan, mix first 7 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and pour over remaining ingredients.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 1 day.
Will keep a week.
Serves 8.

title: egg dip
directions: In a bowl add cream cheese, place grated eggs over cheese. Add chopped pepper; grated onion, melted butter and salt.
Mold with hands and place in center of plate.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish. Cook in a moderately hot oven about 1 hour. Stir well 2 or 3 times while cooking.

title: mary's chow chow
directions: Cook cauliflower until almost soft in one pot.
Cook carrots in another pot until soft, as well as the celery.
Mix all vegetables together.
Make juice with remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cold pack in jars and seal.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour; add all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: hamburger noodle surprise
directions: Saute onions and pepper in bacon drippings until tender but not brown.
Add hamburger meat and cook until mixture falls apart. Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: lemon lite pie
directions: Prepare gelatin according to directions, using half the water. Stir in 10 ice cubes until gelatin thickens.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until serving time.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Place 2 tablespoons bacon grease or oil in a 10-inch black iron skillet and into 375° oven. while mixing cornbread.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° until brown.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of oleo and pour over crushed crackers in a 9-inch or 10-inch pie dish.
Saute onions in 1/4 stick oleo. Spread over cracker layer.
Mix eggs, milk and cheese and pour over onions.
Bake at 350° until set, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients and add apples.
Stir in 1/2 cup nut meats.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon. Toss biscuits in this mixture.
Put raisins or nuts in bottom of a well-greased Bundt or tube pan (optional).
Make layers of biscuits and raisins.

title: diabetic drop cookies
directions: Cook raisins in a little water, about 1/2 cup, until water is almost gone. Add margarine and cool. Add ingredients in order given and drop on greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° until done. These cookies take a little longer than regular cookie dough.
You must refrigerate these cookies or they will mold.
Freezes well.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milks together; add Cool whip and blend until smooth.
Line a 9x13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Layer pudding, then graham crackers, pudding, then graham crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pie shell. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: banana layer cake
directions: Grease pans thoroughly, then dust lightly with flour.
Sift flour once, then measure and sift again with soda and baking powder.
Cream butter, add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add the whole eggs, beating well after the addition of each.
Add sour milk and vanilla to bananas.
Add alternately the flour and banana mixture to butter mixture, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Do not overmix.
Divide evenly into cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, milk and vanilla together in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Dip bread, one slice at a time, into egg mixture.
Cook 2 to 3 pieces at a time in skillet for 3 to 4 minutes, until brown.
Serve with powdered sugar or pancake syrup.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, jello and water. Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.
Add berries. Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Top with whipped topping.

title: curried eggs
directions: Prepare white sauce: melt butter, add flour and make a roux. Add milk, whisking as it thickens.
Add curry powder, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Blend in eggs and mushrooms and gently heat through. Serve on toasted English muffins or toast points.
Serves 8.

title: unbaked peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter and mix in graham cracker crumbs.
Cool a bit; then add peanut butter and icing sugar.
Mix well.

title: custard pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top of filling.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350°.
Bake 35 minutes more.
Makes 1 1/2-inch large (9-inch) pie.

title: my daddy's southern barbecue
directions: This is a mustard based barbecue sauce so it should taste tangy as opposed to sweet like a ketchup based barbecue sauce. This sauce is also great for barbecued chicken.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until all ingredients are mixed well except for some bits of coconut.
Pour into a 10-inch greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cool slightly before serving.

title: after-work stew
directions: Layer potatoes, carrots, celery and onions in slow cooker. Mix beef with salt, basil and pepper in bowl and place on top of vegetables. Combine soup and water. Pour into slow cooker. Cover. Bake on low 8 to 9 hours or until vegetables and meat are tender.

title: stuffed breast of lamb
directions: Cut pocket in end of lamb breast.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Place stuffing in pocket of lamb. Place in baking dish in cold oven.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours and 30 minutes.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate in a covered dish. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Place Crisco in large bowl.
Add boiling water and stir until melted.
Add sugar, cold water and yeast which has been dissolved in warm water, egg, flour and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover with waxed paper and wet towel.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Take out 2 or 3 hours before using.
Shape and allow to rise until almost doubled in size.
Bake in a hot oven at 450° for 7 minutes.

title: bran muffins(regular and microwave)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use as needed.
Bake in well-greased tin at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes in regular oven, six muffins for 2 1/2 minutes on High in microwave.
Keep mix for 6 weeks in refrigerator without spoiling.

title: mediterranean pasta with sausage
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Stir in sauce, olives, and spinach; heat through.
In a large bowl, combine meat sauce with pasta. Toss well.
Coat a 13 x 9 dish with cooking spray.
Pour half of pasta mixture in dish; top with cheese.
Repeat.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: candy cane cake
directions: Stir food coloring and peppermint extract into batter. Carefully pour pink batter around middle of cake, then pour remaining white batter over the cake.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan and top springs back when lightly touched in center.
Cool 10 minutes; invert on a wire rack. Cool completely.
Spread with glaze allowing it to run down the sides; sprinkle with crushed candy canes.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and put in 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with crackers and pour butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients to crumbs.
Take out one cup and set aside.
To first mixture, add milk, soda and egg.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
To remaining 1 cup crumbs add cinnamon and nuts.
Mix well and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: gnocchi
directions: Heat first four ingredients to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Potato Buds, whipping with fork.
Cool.
Add egg, cheese and flour.
Mix and knead well.
If dough is sticky add a handful of flour and work dough.
Roll and cut on floured board to desired size.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a large saucepan, and add soup, grated cheese, onion and sour cream.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour over grated potatoes in large baking dish and mix lightly.
Top with crushed cornflakes and bake, uncovered, in preheated oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine and mix all the ingredients thoroughly.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: In a mixing
bowl,
thoroughly stir together the flour, sugar, baking
powder,
baking
soda and salt.
In a separate bowl combine
the
egg
substitute, corn oil, yogurt, vanilla, bananas and undrained pineapple.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients
and
add
liquid ingredients all at once, stirring until
well
moistened.
Pour
batter
into a 10-inch fluted tube pan, sprayed with nonstick vegetable coating. Bake in preheated 350°
oven	for 65 to70 minutes or until inserted toothpick in center
comes
out clean. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan and
cool
on
wire
rack.	Sift 1 tablespoon powdered sugar over top. Serves 16.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar thoroughly.
Blend in drained fruit cup.
Stir in 3/4 of Cool Whip.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and nuts (if desired).
Chill and serve with meal or as dessert.

title: no cook candy
directions: Cream butter and syrup.
Add other ingredients and mix until smooth.
Roll into balls and mash on wax paper.
Good for kids to make.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add beaten eggs, milk and vanilla. Work in dry ingredients and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake in a moderate oven until nicely browned.

title: one-pot italian spaghetti
directions: Crumble ground beef into a Dutch oven.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until browned, about 10 minutes.
Drain off fat.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix
pineapple
and sugar; let stand awhile.
Add soda, baking powder,
vanilla,
flour and nuts.
Mix by hand.
Pour into ungreased
and
unfloured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine, soup, sour cream and cheese in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with vegetable oil spray.
Put potatoes into dish and pour cheese mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs over casserole and spray lightly with vegetable oil spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil, shiny side up.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar gradually.
Fold in ingredients gradually.
Drop by teaspoons on lined cookie sheet. Put in oven and turn oven off.
Leave until oven is cold.

title: dal
directions: Wash beans; soak overnight.
Drain lentils and cover with boiling water.
Cook, covered, 45 minutes.
Cook until tender. Add a little water, if necessary.
Use small frypan.
Melt butter.
Add curry powder and onions and cook until onions are limp.
Add to lentils.
Add salt and pepper.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Partially freeze meat; thinly slice across the grain into bite size strips.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt; coat meat with flour mixture.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine Raisins and Warm Water in small bowl and let stand 5 minutes, drain.
Combine Raisins, Broccoli, Onion, Celery, Bacon, Cheese in a large bowl and toss well.
In a small bowl, combine Mayonnaise, Sugar and Vinegar; mix well.
Spoon dressing mixture over broccoli mixture.
Toss gently and serve.
Serves 10.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together Bisquick, milk, cheese and parsley flakes.
Spray nonstick cooking spray on baking sheet. Drop batter by tablespoons and bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until brown.
While biscuits are baking, melt butter and garlic powder together in microwave.
Brush on hot biscuits when done.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and spice.
Cool.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand 24 hours before using.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat and add dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
A moist cake.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix everything together and simmer 1 hour.
Can be frozen.
Serve with chips or cornbread. Top with shredded cheese.

title: fattiman (poor man's buckles)
directions: Combine ingredients and beat real well; add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll dough out as thin as you can on a floured board and cut it into diamond shapes.
Put slit in center of each diamond and pull end through.
Fry at 375° until golden brown.
Drain on paper toweling and coat with powdered sugar.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Place in lightly greased casserole; top with chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients except bread crumbs, mixing well.
Spoon mixture over chicken; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine 2 cups berries, water, sugar, cornstarch and salt. Mash and cook.
Put 3 cups of fresh berries in baked pie crust. Pour the cooked sauce over fresh berries.
Serve with whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, then vanilla and sour cream. Add dry ingredients; cut in nuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in 10-inch tube pan.

title: angel food pie
directions: Drain juice from can of pineapple; save and add enough water to juice to equal 1 1/2 cups.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add to the juice mixture in the top of double boiler.
Cook until thick, making sure mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in pineapple and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in with pineapple mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with ground almonds.
Delicious!

title: delicious no-cook candy
directions: In a bowl, mix peanut butter and oats; set aside.
In medium pan, mix together sugar, margarine, milk, cocoa and salt.
Bring to boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Pour over peanut butter mixture; mix thoroughly.
Add coconut; mix well.
Drop by tablespoonful onto wax paper.
Put in refrigerator for an hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Blend thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: garden pea casserole
directions: Spray bottom of 2-quart dish with cooking spray.
Line bottom of dish with drained peas; cover peas with celery soup.
Spread pimientos over soup; spread chestnuts over pimientos.
Put cheese next.
Mix Ritz crackers and margarine together and put on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover dish first 15 minutes of baking, then uncover for remainder of time.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Toss all items in large bowl. Serve over lettuce or other salad greens.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with Cool Whip.
Add pineapple.
You can add marshmallows, coconut or 1 can of drained fruit.
Be sure to drain all other fruit except pineapple.

title: turkey enchiladas
directions: In a fry pan, saute chilies, pepper, onion, garlic and oregano in the oil.
Remove from heat.
Stir together turkey, salt, cheese, sour cream and pepper mixture.
Soak tortillas one at a time in water until soft.
Put turkey mixture in each and roll up. Put in two 9 x 13-inch pans, seam side down.
Stir milk and soup together; pour over enchiladas.
Bake at 300° approximately 30 minutes.
(Cheddar may be used instead of Jack cheese.)
A tomato may be chopped and added to pepper mixture or jalapeno to taste.

title: mexican pie
directions: Combine melted butter with chips, tossing and coating well. Put 2 cups in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In skillet brown meat and onion, drain, add seasoning and mix well.
Add tomato and taco sauce.
Over the chips layer half the corn, half the meat and 6 slices of cheese.
Repeat.
Sprinkle remaining crushed chips over the top in diagonal strips.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until edges bubble.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In a nonstick skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain.
Add the refried beans, oregano, cumin and garlic powder; heat through.
Place three noodles in a 13x9x2 inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray; cover with half of the meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles. combine salsa and water.
Pour over noodles.
Cover and bake at 350° for 60-70 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Spread with sour cream and top with olives, cheese, and onions.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in butter in skillet. Combine with cabbage, 2 cups of the cheese, bread crumbs, salt and pepper in a large baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese; pour half and half over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack in 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sauteed shrimp over linguini
directions: Cook linguini and drain (keep hot).
Stir-fry shrimp or scallops over medium heat in olive oil with 1/2 of the crushed garlic.
Remove from skillet.
(Only cook shrimp until pink on both sides, or they'll be tough.)
Stir-fry zucchini in the same skillet, adding 3 tablespoons soy sauce and rest of crushed garlic.
Add pea pods and cook until pea pods are shiny, being careful not to overcook.
Add basil.
Add 1/4 cup water, if pan gets dry, then add the shrimp into the zucchini mixture.
Last, before serving, add sliced tomatoes and cook for about 5 minutes more.
Add all of this to drained linguini and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: henry's goulash
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain on paper towels.
In a large boiler, put pork and beans, chopped tomatoes and catsup.
Let mixture come to a boil, stirring well.
Add ground beef.
Let simmer on low heat for about 30 minutes. Good with creamed potatoes and biscuits.

title: beatrice's flank steak
directions: Lay steak
in
shallow
pan.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over
meat.
Turn
over
to
marinate
both
sides. Cover and refrigerate
for
to 8 hours or overnight.
(Drain and rescue marinade you
can
save
and
use it on hamburger or chicken if you wish.)
Broil steak over very hot coals for 8 to 10 minutes each side or cook in frying pan over high heat for 3 to 5 minutes each
side.
Brush
with marinade, cooking 8 to 10 minutes longer.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Cut up all vegetables and boil until almost tender.
Drain off water; mix all ingredients together and put in cans.
Cold pack for 1/2 hour.

title: butter frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.

title: shells with sausage and peppers
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package, drain.
Toss with 2 tablespoons olive oil and set aside.
Take casing or skin off sausage, break up, cook and stir sausage until well done.
Drain. Stir in wine and cook 10 minutes.
Remove mixture from skillet, set aside.
Add remaining oil to skillet along with onion and peppers. Cook and stir until crisp and tender.
Add garlic, cook 30 seconds. Add sausage with parsley and heat.
Add with salt to pasta in bowl, toss.

title: velveeta cheese spread salsa dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta process cheese spread and Pace picante sauce in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High for 5 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or broiled green, red and yellow pepper wedges.
Makes 3 cups.

title: drop donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop from dessertspoon into hot grease.
As bottom cooks it will turn itself over.
Place powdered sugar in bag and shake if desired.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate the eggs.
Whip the egg whites and add 8 tablespoons of sugar while beating.
When finished, place in refrigerator while rest of cake is being mixed.
Cream the butter and add gradually the rest of the sugar.
Whip until light.
Add egg yolks, about 2 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and cream a little at a time.
Whip until the mixture is as light as possible on low speed.
With mixer at low speed, whip in the egg whites only long enough to mix well.
Pour batter into a lightly greased tube pan 10 inches in diameter and 4 inches deep. Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.

title: grandma's chocolate sauce
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Mix together with whisk.
Add evaporated milk.
Stir well.
Cook on medium-high heat.
Boil rapidly for 3 to 4 minutes.
Take off heat and add butter and vanilla.
Great over vanilla ice cream.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until thick.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: manhattan meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, sausage, onion, cracker crumbs and 2 eggs. Make into balls.
Fry until brown.
Drain off grease.
Pour barbecue sauce and peach preserves over meatballs.
Stir.
Simmer for one hour.
(Can be simmered in crock-pot for several hours.) Delicious served as a main dish or as an hors d'oeuvres.
